Commentary: Right on the money! Anderson serves a length ball, right on the off pole. A bit of away movement on that one but Sharma blocks it from the crease.
Another outswinger but this starts outside off, making it easy for Sharma to leave it.
A touch fuller and on the fourth stump. Sharma thinks of playing it but leaves it in the end.
First run of the Test! On a length, on leg. Sharma works it past square leg and gets off the mark.
Fuller ball, but way outside off. Rahul strides forward and then leaves it alone.
Short of a length, around the sixth stump. Rahul has no qualms in leaving this one.
Robinson bowls a length delivery, in the channel outside off. Sharma is aware of his off pole and leaves this one.
This lands on a length, around off and comes back in. Sharma leaves it on length as the ball goes over the stumps.
Back of a length, on leg. Sharma looks to work it away to the leg side but gets hit high on the pads.
Ollie Robinson bowls a fuller ball, on the fourth stump. Sharma offers the full face of the bat and blocks this one out from the crease.
On a length, around off. Sharma gets behind the line of the ball and pushes it towards point.
Beaten! This lands on a length, just outside off. Sharma is forced to play at it but the ball nips away and goes past the outside edge.
FOUR! First boundary of the game! Anderson bowls it fuller and outside off. Rahul leans into it nicely and drives it through covers for a boundary. Top shot.
FOUR! Edged and four! On a length, on off. Rahul gets the outside edge while looking to bowl, but the ball goes past gully and runs to the fence.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Rahul comes forward and keeps his bat behind the pads to leave it.
Back of a length, right in the channel outside off. Rahul looks to block it but brings his bat back at the last moment.
A touch fuller, outside off. Rahul comes on the front foot and blocks it well.
Nicely played. Length ball, on leg. Sharma works it towards deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, lands outside off and comes back in. Rahul covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
Tap and run. Length ball, on off. Rahul taps it with soft hands to the off side. Both the batters set off for the single right away and complete it with ease.
On a length, around off. This nips away a bit but Sharma is behind the line of the ball. He pushes it towards point for one.
A nice outswinger, but this starts way outside off. Rahul gets on the front foot and then leaves it.
Length ball, on off. This comes back in with the angle as Ollie Robinson is bowling over the wicket. Rahul clips it past square leg for one.
Short of a length, around off. Rahul stays back and pushes it towards point.
James Anderson bowls a length ball, just outside off and gets it to come back in. Rahul leaves it on length and the ball goes over off pole.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, this lands outside off and comes back in. Rahul stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Back of a length, just outside off. Rahul works it with soft hands towards the gully fielder.
FOUR! That is a lovely shot! Fuller ball, outside off. Rahul puts in a stride and drives it past point for another boundary.
Ollie Robinson lets it go on a length, on the sixth stump. Sharma leaves this one with ease.
Good-length delivery, lands on off and comes back in. Sharma is hit on the pads while looking to clip it away.
Fuller ball, around off. Sharma puts in a stride and blocks it out.
Length ball, on leg. Sharma looks to block it but the ball bounces a bit more and hits him on the pads.
Length ball, down the leg side. Sharma misses the flick. Jonny Bairstow dives to his left and collects it well.

FOUR! Just short of the fielder! On a length, around off. Rohit Sharma punches it. The ball goes towards mid on. James Anderson moves to his right but the ball bounces just short of him and goes past him. It then runs to the fence.

Back of a length, outside off. Rahul looks to block but gets the inside edge. The ball goes past the stumps and past the keeper too. It goes towards fine leg but the fielder chases it and keeps it to two.
Beaten! That is well bowled! Length ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Rahul is beaten as he looks to block it.
Nicely played. Shorter ball, outside off. Pushed past point for one.
Really well played. Fuller ball, on off. Sharma offers the full face of the bat and punches it past mid off. The fielder chases it and keeps it down to a couple.
And again! Length ball, around off. Sharma leans into it and times it past mid off. The fielder chases it yet again and keeps it down to a couple.
Peach of a delivery! This comes in with the angle and lands on a length, on off. Sharma looks to block it from the crease but the ball shapes away and goes past the outside edge.
On a length, around off. Rahul covers his stumps and then leaves it.
A touch fuller, on off. Rahul taps it with soft hands towards the slip cordon.
Length ball, wide outside off. Rahul strides forward and then leaves it alone.
Beaten! Ollie Robinson bowls a length ball, in the channel outside off. Rahul comes forward and looks to block but is beaten.
Play and a miss! Fuller ball, outside off. Rahul is drawn into the drive but gets no bat on it again.
A touch shorter, outside off. Rahul leaves it alone now.
Woakes starts with a fuller ball, on off. Sharma blocks it out with ease.
Outswinger but this starts outside off. Sharma leaves this one alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Sharma stays in the crease and blocks it.
Play and a miss! Full ball, outside off. Sharma is glued to his crease as he looks to drive. The ball shapes away sharply and goes past the bat. Jonny Bairstow dives to his right and collects it.
Back of a length, around off. Blocked out from the crease.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Welcome back, Chris Woakes! That is a jaffa! Woakes bowls it touch shorter, right around off. Sharma is forced to play at it and hangs his bat out. The ball nips away and takes the outside edge. Jonny Bairstow moves to his right and does the rest. The patience of the English pacers has been finally rewarded!
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Chris Woakes

Commentary: A touch fuller, on off. Blocked out by Rahul.
Full ball, around off. Rahul gets the outside edge while looking to block. But since he has played it with soft hands, the ball bounces on its way to the gully fielder.
Length ball, on off. Rahul looks to block but gets the inside edge back on the pads.
Fuller now, but down the leg side. Rahul misses the flick.
Length ball, outside off. Rahul blocks it with his bat and pads together. There is an appeal for LBW by some of the fielders in the slip cordon but not a big one.
Full ball, on leg. Worked to mid-wicket by Rahul.
Full ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara gets on the front foot and blocks it.
Back of a length, around off. Pujara taps it to the off side and sets off for a run, but Rahul sends him back as the cover fielder runs in towards the ball very fast.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out by Pujara.
Fuller ball, outside off. Pujara leaves this with ease.
On a length, just outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara hangs back and leaves it again.
This comes back in! Lands on a length, on off and comes back in sharply. Cheteshwar Pujara is hit high on the pads as he looks to clip it away.
Fuller ball, wide outside off. Left alone.
Beaten now! On a length, on off. Rahul looks to block it by coming forward but the ball goes past the edge.
On a length, outside off. Rahul leaves it.
A touch shorter and quite wide outside off. Left alone yet again.
Rahul almost plays at it! Full ball, just outside off. Rahul thinks of going for the drive but misses.

NOT OUT! The ball is going down the leg stump. Fuller ball, lands on off and comes back in. Rahul looks to block but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal put in for LBW but turned down. Joe Root does not look too convinced but takes the review in the end. The replay rolls in. UltraEdge shows no bat on that one but Ball Tracker shows the ball going down the leg stump.
Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone.

Another appeal for LBW! Length ball, lands on off and comes back in. Cheteshwar Pujara gets hit on the pads while looking to block. There is an appeal for LBW but turned down. England do not review this one. Good decision as the replay shows that Cheteshwar Pujara got an inside edge on that one.
Length ball, down leg. Pujara misses the flick.
On a length, around off. Pujara blocks it out well.
Length ball, on off. Pujara pushes it back to the bowler. Woakes gets to his left and stops the ball.
Six maidens in a row for England! Length ball, around leg. Cheteshwar Pujara gets hit on the pads as he looks to block it.
Fuller ball, around off. Rahul blocks it out well.
Length ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Rahul puts in a stride but keeps his bat behind the front pad to leave it.
An outswinger now. This lands outside off and comes back in. Rahul leaves it. Bairstow moves to his left and gets hit on the gloves.
Fuller ball, on leg. Rahul works it to the leg side.

OUT! LBW! That is out! The incoming delivery gets rid of Rahul! England are breathing fire out there. This is really well bowled by Ollie Robinson. He serves a length ball, it lands outside off and comes in. Rahul looks to block but gets hit on the pads. Ollie Robinson is convinced that this is out and appeals loudly. The umpire thinks about this for a while and then raises the finger. Rahul has a word with Pujara and then reviews it. There is no bat on that one. The Ball Tracker rolls in, it shows umpire's call on impact and the ball is hitting the stumps!
Howout: lbw b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone by Kohli.
FOUR! Thank you very much, says Cheteshwar Pujara! Length ball, on the pads. Pujara whips it to the square leg fence. These are the first runs conceded by Woakes in this game.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, around off. Pujara blocks it well.
Fuller ball, around off. Pujara blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length, around off. Pujara pushes it to the off side.
Length ball, on the pads. Pujara works it towards square leg.
Back of a length, outside off. Kohli has no qualms in leaving this one.
Full ball, on the pads. Kohli shuffles across to flick it but gets hit on the pads. The ball goes towards fine leg for a couple of leg byes.
Back of a length, outside off. Kohli covers his stumps and leaves it.
Top shot for no run. Length ball, on off. Kohli nails the drive but straight towards the man at short cover.
Fuller ball, on off. Kohli gets forward and blocks it well.
Robinson bowls a fuller ball, outside off. Kohli looks to block but gets it from the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Length ball, on leg. Pujara gets hit high on the pads while looking to block this one.
Short of a length, on off. Pujara works it towards short leg.
On a length, outside off. Pujara leans forward and leaves it alone.
On a length again, on off. Pujara blocks it with ease now.
A touch fuller, outside off. Pujara leaves this one with ease.
Fuller ball, quite wide outside off. Pujara thinks of playing it but leaves it in the end.
Back of a length, outside off. Kohli leaves this one alone.
Fuller ball, on off. Kohli gets on the front foot and blocks it out.
Full and right on the off pole. Kohli plays it with soft hands towards gully.
This comes back in! This lands on a length, on off and comes back in. Kohli looks to block but gets hit high on the pads.
Another cracking drive for nothing. Full ball, outside off. Kohli nails the drive straight towards mid off.

FOUR! OH MY WORD! That is a gorgeous stroke by Kohli! Anderson bowls a fuller ball, outside off. Kohli shuffles across a bit and then whips it to the left of mid on. The ball races to the long on fence in no time.
On a length, outside off. Left alone by Pujara.
Back of a length, but wide enough for Pujara to leave it with ease.
Another length ball, outside off. Another leave by Pujara.
A touch fuller, on off. Pujara blocks this one.
Another full-length delivery, around off. Pujara is solid in his defence yet again.
Length ball, outside off. Pujara is aware of his off pole and leaves it.
Back of a length, outside off. Left alone by Kohli.
This one nips away quite a bit but starts outside off. Kohli leaves it alone.
Length ball, on off. Kohli works it past square leg for one.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! James Anderson finally strikes! This is a work of art by Anderson! He bowls a length ball, on off. The pacer pushes it in towards the batter through the air but gets it to shape away after landing. Pujara looks to block but the away movement means that he gets the outside edge. Jonny Bairstow takes it with ease. The umpire takes a while but raises the finger in the end. This has been a sensational start for England!
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b James Anderson

Commentary: Back of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone. Jonny Bairstow moves across to his left and collects the ball.
Fuller ball, outside off. Kohli leaves this one with ease.
This lands on a length, outside off and comes back in. Kohli covers his stumps and leaves it.
Length ball, in the line of the stumps. Kohli blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Left alone by Kohli.
Length ball, on leg. Kohli works it past square leg for a single.
Length ball, but wide outside off. Jadeja has no interest in playing that one.

Length ball, around off. Kohli looks to leave it a bit too late and gets the inside edge. The ball goes past the stumps and past the keeper. A single is taken. James Anderson smiles wryly at Kohli while walking back and a few polite words are exchanged.
Length ball, outside off. Jadeja leaves it alone.
Fuller ball, on the pads. Jadeja whips it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Back of a length, angling across the off pole. Jadeja leaves it alone now.

Appeal for LBW! Full ball, lands on off and comes back in. Jadeja looks to work it away but gets hit on the pads. The appeal is put in but the ball is likely heading down the leg stump and the umpire shakes his head.
On a length, around off. Jadeja stays in his crease and blocks it.
Back of a length, on off. Kohli plays it with soft hands towards third man. Haseeb Hameed chases it from backward point and keeps it down to a couple of runs.
Fuller ball, on off. Kohli looks to block it but gets it from the inner half to the leg side.
FOUR! That is a cracking shot by Kohli! Full ball, in the line of the stumps. Kohli leans into it and times it to the long on fence.
Back of a length, on off. Blocked out by Kohli.

FOUR! Second boundary of the over. Length ball, on off. Kohli gets the outside edge but the ball bounces after hitting the bat. It goes past the slip cordon and the point fielder cannot chase it down. 50 up for India!
Back of a length, on off. Blocked out by Kohli.
Fuller ball, outside off. Jadeja leaves this one alone.
Full and wide outside off. Jadeja gets forward and then leaves it alone.
This comes back in! Wow, how did that miss the stumps? This is fuller, just outside off. Jadeja leaves it but the ball nips back in and goes just past the off pole.

The bounce saves Jadeja! Length ball, lands on off and comes back in. Jadeja leaves it and gets hit high on the pads. The appeal is turned down as Jadeja is hit high on the pads. The replay confirms that the ball was going over the stumps.
Length ball, outside off. Jadeja looks to leave it a bit too late. He gets the inside edge towards the slip cordon. This is excellent bowling by Anderson.
Fuller and wider outside off. This time, Jadeja leaves it with ease.
Length ball, on off. Pushed past covers for one.
Fuller ball, on off. Jadeja blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Jadeja leaves it alone with ease.
Nicely played. Length ball, around off. Jadeja gets on the front foot to block it.
Beaten! Length ball, outside off. Jadeja looks to block but is beaten. Root gets a bit excited at first slip but finds no support from others.
Length ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Jadeja leaves it to end the session. That is Lunch on Day 1!
Woakes starts with one on a length and outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to this one.
Slightly closer to the off pole this time, shapes away again. Another easy leave for Kohli.

FOUR! Shot! What a wonderful way to get things underway in this session for India's skipper! Just creamed! Fuller and outside off. Kohli leans into it and strokes it through covers. It races away. That same shot gets him in trouble but also gives him a lot of runs.
Two leg byes! Woakes looks to get this one to shape away from the leg pole, it does not swing, Kohli looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and goes towards fine leg. Two leg byes.
Gets his line right this time and bowls it on off, Kohli blocks it out.
A harmless ball to end! Outside off, some movement away. Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Outside off and on a length. Left alone.
Slightly fuller this time, Jadeja pushes it cautiously towards mid off.
Yet another ball outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to this one.
Watchful from Jadeja! Outside off, left alone. This lands and moves away initially but then as it passes the batter, starts to swing back in late. Bairstow does well to get hold of it.

FOUR! Through the vacant gully region! Jadeja is not confident with those drives! Once again he tentatively pushes at it which is fuller and outside off. Probably in two minds whether he should be playing at it or not. It flies off the outside edge, with no gully in place, it goes past the slip cordon and runs to the fence.
A short one to end, Jadeja ducks under it.
Good length and on middle, Kohli is solid in defense.
Another one which shapes away but from outside off, Kohli covers his off pole and lets it go.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Root spills his opposite number! He reacts quite late. He probably thinks that Burns at second slip will go for it. Some luck for Kohli. You need some of that in these conditions. However, that is once again a tentative poke from Kohli. It is on a length and around off, the ball shapes away. Kohli pokes at it away from his body, it goes off the outside edge between first and second slip. Burns watches it go past him. Root reacts late to his right and goes with one hand but the ball does not stick. It goes behind for one. Probably Burns is not used to standing at second slip as he was fielding at gully for most of the series. Since Bairstow is keeping in this game, Burns takes that role of fielding in the slips. We saw Jonny Bairstow take a similar catch in the last game where he dived to his left with one hand. Also, Root and Burns are standing way too close, and hence, that confusion. Can Kohli make most of this life? For now, both Burns and Root are smiling it off but they would surely rue this if Kohli scores big here. Also, the ball just kept swinging away after it took the edge which made it a little more difficult for Root.
Good length and on off, blocked.
FOUR! Clipped away! That is a gift! On the pads, Jadeja works it nicely through square leg. Boundary.
A leave to end! Outside off, left alone.
Solid! Length and on off, defended off the back foot.
Well bowled! Overton is mainly getting it to shape away, this time gets it back in from outside off. Not enough though to make Kohli play.
Yet again outside off, Kohli makes a leave again.
Overton goes wide of the crease now and angles it into the middle pole, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Excellent bowling! On middle, Kohli shuffles across, covers the away movment and plays it back to the bowler.
As solid as it can get! On a length yet again, Kohli pushes it to covers.
Fuller in length and outside off, left alone. Once again the ball shapes back in late. Bairstow does well to stop it with a dive to his right.
Good length and on off, Jadeja pushes it to covers.
On the fuller side yet again, outside off. Jadeja watches it go to the keeper.
Jadeja plays that late! This one comes back in late, it is fuller and outside off. The ball tails back in. Jadeja gets his bat down in time and blocks.
Outside off, Jadeja lets it be.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Another one bites the dust! This time the catch is taken. It is not Kohli but Jadeja who has to depart. Not a bad wicket too! Woakes has another one. This is on a length, it lands on off and then holds its line. Jadeja looks to defend but does so inside the line of the ball. It goes off the outside edge and Root this time takes a good low catch at first slip. The move to send Jadeja up the order does not work. A stand that was building has been cut short. India slip further. Jadeja actually played that with hard hands, he pushed at it, had he played it with soft hands, the ball may not have carried.
Howout: c Joe Root b Chris Woakes

Commentary: Outside off, left alone.
Angled into the pads, Kohli works it down to fine leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Rahane blocks it out.
Angled into the pads, Rahane is off the mark as he works it through square leg. He needs to step up here, India need him to fire along with their skipper.
Angled into the middle pole, Kohli works it to square leg.
Tap and run! On off, Kohli pushes it to cover for one.
Slightly fuller, shapes away. Blocked nicely.
Quite similar to the delivery he edged earlier, this time though he leaves it alone.
On middle, this one shapes away. Kohli looks to defend, it goes off the outer half to cover.

Not needed, just not needed at this stage of the game! That is not a line Kohli should be playing at. Gets away with one there. Length and well outside off, Kohli pushes at it, the ball flies past the outside edge.
Angled into the pads, Kohli works it through square leg for one.

NOT OUT! Going over! The Indian dressing room will breathe a huge sigh of relief! That looked out to me though. Good review from India. Brilliant from Woakes again. This lands outside off and then comes back in. Woakes has been taking the ball away but this time gets it back in. Rahane looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pads. A huge shout and the finger is raised. Rahane reviews after a chat with his skipper. Replays roll in and they show that it is going over.
On middle, blocked.
Just outside off, left alone.
Just outside off, Kohli does not play at it. This one is a good leave, it is in the channel where Kohli tends to poke.
This one is well wide outside off, left alone.
A quick run! Angled into middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
Good length and on off, Rahane plays it late and to gully.
Good length and on off, Kohli plays it towards cover.
Back of a length and on off, Kohli defends it onto the ground.

FOUR! That is exquisite! Lovely stroke! The key here is he gets his front foot towards the line of the ball. Fuller and outside off, Kohli creams it through covers for a boundary. He gets into the 30s.
Close! Angled into the middle pole, Kohli looks to defend it out, it goes off the inner half towards fine leg for one.
Solid! On off, Rahane gets right behind the line and defends.
This one comes back in! This lands outside off, jags back in. Rahane looks to defend but misses to get hit above the knee roll.
On middle, Kohli pushes it back to the bowler.
Well left! Once again this is just outside off, an area where Kohli tends to has a go. Kohli leaves it alone again. After that dropped catch, he has been a little more careful.
Another one on a length and around off, defended nicely.
Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.

Yet another good leave! Overton goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole, very easily Rahane could have come forward and looked to defend because of the angle. But he watches it till the very end and lets it go after covering his off pole.
Slightly fuller, Rahane pushes it to mid off.
This one is quite wide outside off, Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Another one well wide outside off, Kohli does not play at it. Not a lot of carry on that one.

Three more! Shorter and outside off, Kohli just goes back and times it. Hameed at point dives to his right but fails to stop it. The fielder at cover runs towards the ball, slides and stops it. Saves a run for his side.
Fuller and outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to this one.
Another one well outside off, Rahane does not play at it.
BEATEN! A beauty! This time Anderson gets it to start from off, it moves away nicely. Rahane pushes at it and is beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, Kohli pushes it to mid off.

FOUR LEG BYES! Half an appeal but nothing! This lands on middle and then shapes back in. Kohli looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and races to the fine leg fence. It was clearly going down leg.
FOUR! Into the 40s now is Kohli! Trademark stuff from him! This is full and outside off, Kohli leans into it and strokes it through covers. No chance of stopping that.
Angled into middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Really well played in the end! This is fuller and outside off, shapes away. Rahane at first looks to play at it but then leaves it.
Well outside off, left alone.

FOUR! That is as good a cover drive as you will see! He just uses the pace of the bowler there. Fuller and around off, Kohli times it beautifully, it races past mid off, through extra cover for a boundary. A lot more confidence in those cover drives in this innings so far from Kohli.
Outside off, left alone.
Angled into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On off, blocked.
Fuller and on off, Kohli pushes it to mid off.
Fuller and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
That has gone over the off pole. Risky leave! Length and just outside off, left alone, probably on length. It goes over the off pole.
Two! Rahane finds the gap now! Fuller and outside off, he just pushes it through covers for two.
Slightly fuller and outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Two more and the 100 is up for India! On the pads, Rahane works it fine. They take one slowly but then realize that there is another run on offer, the batters go for it and complete it.
On middle, defended nicely.
Just outside off, Kohli covers the off pole and makes a leave.
This one is wider outside off, not played at.
Down the leg side this time, Kohli looks to flick but misses.
FOUR! Nicely guided in the end and he moves to 49! Shorter and just outside off, Kohli plays it late. He guides it past gully and it races away to the third man fence.

Quick run, Rahane pulls out the dive to make it in. The fielder bends down, picks the ball, underarms it at the striker's end but misses his shy. That is 50 for Kohli! He was dropped earlier on and is making the most of the life he got! He has been getting fifties though but can he get a ton is the big question? Needs to because India are behind in the game right now. Coming to the ball now, a back-of-a-length ball on off, Kohli drops it towards cover and takes one. That was not a dive from Rahane, he actually accelerated right towards the end as he was slow to take off. He just fell onto the ground because of the extra effort.
Another good leave from Rahane! Around off, the ball holds its line. Not played at by Rahane.
Not this time says Rahane! On off, Kohli plays it towards cover. The skipper wants a run but is sent back by his deputy.
Fuller and outside off, this is well wide, left alone.
That is a beauty! Outswinger, outswinger and now the one that comes in that too after landing outside off. It cuts Kohli into half as he tries to block. Whizzes past the inside edge. Excellent stuff.
Good length and on off, Kohli pushes it to mid off.
On off, Kohli is solid in defense.
Another one on middle, Kohli works it to mid-wicket.
Another leave as it is another harmless ball outside off.
Attacks the stumps this time and lands it on middle, blocked.

Almost! The hesitation almost costs Rahane! This starts on off and then shapes away. Rahane initially looks to play at it but then seeing the ball shape away, he tries to leave. It hits the under edge, lands and goes just past the off pole.
On middle, Rahane flicks but towards mid on.
Outside off, Rahane does not fiddle with it.
A maiden then! On middle, this is played back to the bowler.
Another delivery which is outside off, Kohli leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Kohli pushes it to mid off.
Just outside off, Kohli does not play at it.
Kohli is leaving the ball well here! Outside off, Kohli watches it go to the keeper.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! There is the wicket England were looking for! The stand that was looking really good and Kohli who looked all set for a big one is walking back. Ollie Robinson does the trick for his side yet again. Once again Kohli gets past the fifty-run mark and then gets out. This is shorter and on off, it lands and then straightens a touch. Kohli tries to play it with a closed face of the bat, he tries to play it on the leg side and that costs him. It goes off the outside edge to Jonny Bairstow, who takes another catch. England are on top again. They are just a wicket away now from entering the tail of this Indian side. No matter, how good you are, you are never completely in when batting in such conditions.
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Fuller, shapes away from outside off. Left alone.
Outside off, not played at by Rahane.
Yet another leave as this is again bowled outside off. James Anderson is bowling in the right channels.
Third leave in a row! Another harmless ball outside off.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
BEATEN AGAIN! Length and on off, this lands and shapes away. Rahane looks to defend but is beaten.
On middle, defended. A maiden by Anderson.
Fuller ball, wide outside off. Pant leaves this one.
On a length, but wide enough for Pant to leave it with ease.
Fuller ball, outside off. Worked towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball, wide outside off. Ollie Robinson wants Pant to drive at it but the southpaw leaves it.

Just a matter of time before Pant attempted that! Length ball, outside off. Pant steps down the track and goes for the wild heave but misses. Robinson has a smile on his face and he would want Pant to play more like this.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone
Good length and on off, blocked out by Rahane.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one. Rahane needs to play a big knock here for his team.
Outside off, another leave.
On off, Pant pushes it to mid off.
Another one that swings away a lot but the line is well outside off. Left alone by the Indian keeper.
Another one well outside off, Pant does not fiddle with it.
Robinson angles it into the middle pole. Rahane blocks it from the crease.
Fuller ball, around off. Rahane blocks it out yet again.
Outside off, not played at.
Quick run! On off, this is played towards cover for one.
On middle, Pant works it on the leg side.

Another delivery which is not played at as it is well outside off. England have bowled really well to Pant here. It is not often that you see the southpaw yet to get off the mark despite facing 13 deliveries.
Angled into the pads, Rahane looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Outside off, Rahane lets it go to the keeper.
Left again. On a length, outside off. Rahane puts in a stride forward and then leaves it.
Overton is still getting it to shape away but he needs to attack the stumps more. This is outside off. Rahane will leave it all day.
Better! On a length and on off, defended nicely.

Direct hit and England could have had another wicket! Total confusion! On off, this is pushed towards cover. Rahane wants one, Pant is not sure, Rahane does take a start and so does Pant. The latter then realizes it is in the gap and goes for the run. The fielder picks it up and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. The last thing that India would want at this stage is a run out.
Short and on the body, Rahane pulls. He is not in total control, it goes towards fine leg for one.
Around off, Pant plays it to point.
Good shot to get off the mark! On the pads, this is worked nicely through mid-wicket for two. 15 balls is what it took for Pant to get off the mark.
Outside off, Pant is not poking at those. Makes another leave.
And again, plants his front foot forward and just lets this one which is outside off, go to the keeper.
Outside off, Pant leaves it alone yet again.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Fuller and outside off, Rahane times it well through covers. This one races away to the fence. This will do his confidence a world of good.
Short ball, Rahane pulls again, not in control again, this goes towards square leg for one more.
Short again, Pant pulls again but to square leg.
Short and on the body, this is pulled towards square leg for one.

OUT! FINGERS UNDER THE BALL AND RAHANE HAS BEEN GIVEN HIS MARCHING ORDERS! Just before Tea, England strike. The last recognized pair has been separated. Once again a batter falls to a delivery that shapes away. An outswinger, it starts just outside off and shapes away further. Rahane pushes at it with hard hands. It goes off the outside edge towards Moeen Ali at third slip. He dives forward and seems to have taken it inches above the ground. The TV umpire is called to check and replays show that just as his hands hit the ground, the ball seems to be popping out but Moeen Ali hangs on. England are now into the bowling all-rounders.
Howout: c Moeen Ali b Craig Overton

Commentary: Tharkur is off the mark! This one lands on middle, shapes away. Thakur looks to defend with a small stride, it goes off the outer half through backward point for two.
On middle, Pant works it towards mid-wicket for one.
Two more! Outside off, this is pushed through covers for two.
On middle, blocked.
Slightly fuller, this one comes back in, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Now the outswinger, it lands on off, Thakur plays it back to the bowler again.
On off, Thakur keeps it out! THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Back of a length, on off. Pant looks to block but gets the inside edge back on the pads.
FOUR! There comes the boundary! Short of a length, outside off. Pant dances down the track and smacks it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, around off. Pant is solid in his defence of this one.
Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone now.
Full and wide outside off. Pant covers his stumps and then leaves it.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to mid off. The fielder throws the ball to the other end but misses his shy. The batters take a quick single.
Back of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Fuller ball, around off. Pant defends it from the crease.

DROPPED! Length ball, outside off. The ball angles away from the off stump. Pant looks to block but gets the edge. Craig Overton is at third slip and he dives to his right. He gets his hand to it but drops. Overton came in front of Rory Burns, who was at second slip. The replay shows that the ball would have gone straight towards Burns!
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, but wide outside off. Pant makes an easy leave.

OUT! TAKEN! Craig Overton would be delighted with that! This is a rash shot by Pant. This is slower ball, on a length, wide outside off. Pant comes down the track and looks to smack it down the ground. He gets it from the toe end of the bat. Now, England had planned this well. They had sent the man at mid off a few steps back as they expected Pant to play this stroke. Moeen Ali takes an easy catch and sends back India's keeper.
Howout: c Moeen Ali b Chris Woakes

Commentary: Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, down the leg side. Thakur misses the flick.
Length ball, on leg. Thakur works it to fine leg for one.
Beaten! This lands on a length, outside off. Yadav looks to block it but is beaten.
Fuller ball, around off. Blocked out.
Full ball, on leg. Yadav looks to flick it away but gets hit on the pads. An appeal is put in but the ball is probably sliding down the leg pole.
FOUR! That is some shot! Back of a length, on the body. Thakur whips it hard to the square leg fence. The man at deep backward square leg has no chance.
FOUR! PUMPED BY THAKUR! Fuller ball, on off. Thakur punches it hard straight down the ground for a boundary.
More runs for Thakur! Fuller ball, on off. Pushed past the bowler towards long off. The man from mid off chases it, dives and saves a run for his team.
Fuller ball, on off. Worked towards mid-wicket.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone by Yadav.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to mid off.
SIX! High and handsome by Thakur! This is some batting by Thakur. Length ball, on off. Thakur pumps it over the long off fence for a maximum.
Length ball, on off. Punched down the ground. The man at mid off has been moved quite straight now. He collects it on the bounce.
Full ball, on leg. Thakur whips it away for one.
Full again, around off. Yadav heaves it towards mid on.
Length ball, on off. Yadav pushes it to covers.
Yadav survives as he blocks out this length ball towards the bowler.
Just short! Fuller and on off, Thakur looks to belt it over mid off, who is a little deep. It goes more off the splice and lands short of mid off.
Another swing but miss! Short and outside off, Thakur swings really hard but misses.
FOUR! Powered! Stand-and-deliver stuff! Short and on middle, Thakur pulls it hard through mid-wicket. The ball races away to the fence as there is no one in the deep.
Slightly early in the shot! It is a slower ball, short and outside off. Thakur swings early, it goes off the bottom towards mid-wicket.
Very full and on off, Thakur works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Another boundary! Thakur is playing a gem of a knock here! Angled into the pads, he whips it over mid-wicket. There is a fielder in the deep but it goes wide of him for another boundary.
On middle, this is defended nicely.
Just outside off, Yadav does not fiddle with it.
An appeal but turned down! It came off the flap! Shorter and on off. Yadav hops and looks to whip it, it goes off the flap of the pad to the keeper.
More runs! Back of a length and on off, it lands and moves away. Yadav looks to defend, this goes off the outside edge down to third man for two runs.
FOUR! Whipped away! Yadav joins the party now! Fuller and on middle, this is whipped through mid-wicket. It races away to the fence. Frustrating for England at the moment.
Almost! Fuller and on middle, Yadav looks to flick again, he gets an inside edge onto the pads. Had he got no bat, he would have been a candidate for LBW.
Ouch! That might have hurt! Length and this one comes back in from outside off. Thakur looks to flick but misses to gets hit near the box.
Looks to hit that hard again but misses! Short and outside off, Thakur tries to pull but misses.
In the air... safe! Fuller and outside off, Thakur looks to go over covers, mistimes it, it lands safe ahead of the fielders running after it. Two taken.
SIX! Smacked! Into the crowd! There is a fielder in the deep but it does not matter! A slower one on off, Thakur whips it well over the mid-wicket fence.
Angled into the pads, Thakur looks to flick but misses. It hits the pads. An appeal for LBW but it is turned down. Going down leg probably.

FOUR! Over the slip cordon! Luck too favoring India! Outside off and fuller. Thakur has a swing at it, it goes off the outside edge over Root at second slip and down to the third man fence. Thakur into the 40s.

Confusion but safe in the end! Length and on off, Yadav looks to defend, this goes more off the outer half down to third man. The fielder gives it a chase. They take two. Thakur wants the strike so goes for the third. Umesh is late in taking off. The keeper collects it and then fires it at the bowler's end. He misses.

It seems like it is a drop! Bairstow just got the wrong side of it. The frustration continues! A short one down the leg side, Thakur looks to pull but it goes off the glove behind the stumps. Bairstow runs to his left, he seems to have overrun it. He tries to get to his right and gets his gloves to it but drops it.
On off, Thakur blocks it.
FOUR! Slapped! Not off the middle but he gets the result he wanted! Shorter and outside off, this is hit off the lower part but over mid off for a boundary by Thakur.

SIX! SMACKED! Fifty for Thakur! Thakur into the side for his bowling, he though needed to fire with the bat and does so. What a counter-attacking knock it is turning out to be. He is absolutely delighted. He can't relax now. Needs to keep going. Short and on middle, this is pulled, it is nailed over the square leg fence for a biggie.
A dot to end! On off, this is hit to mid off. No runs.
Length ball, on off. Yadav blocks it out.
Length ball, on leg. Yadav works it past square leg for one.
Back of a length, on off. Blocked out by Thakur.
Length ball, outside off. Drilled to mid on.
FOUR! Stand and deliver! Short of a length, outside off. Thakur smacks it past covers. The man from long off gets across to his left but cannot get to the ball.

OUT! LBW! Three reds and the Shardul Thakur show ends! This has been a brilliant knock by Thakur. India would have been in a dire situation if Thakur hadn't scored runs here. Length ball, on middle and leg. Thakur looks to heave it away but misses. The ball hits his pads and Woakes and co put in a big appeal. It is turned down though. England review this. No bat on that one and three reds on Ball Tracker send Thakur back!
Howout: lbw b Chris Woakes

Commentary: OUT! BUMRAH IS RUN OUT! Plenty of drama and a wicket on that ball! Length ball, outside off. Yadav looks to heave it away but gets the outside edge. Craig Overton is at first slip, he leaps and gets his hands to it but spills. The batters try to sneak in a run. Rory Burns is at second slip, he gathers the ball and fires a direct hit at the keeper's end. The TV umpire is called in and the replay shows that Bumrah is short of the crease. Mohammed Siraj is the last batter.
Howout: run out (Craig Overton / Rory Burns)

Commentary: Length ball, on off. Pushed past covers for one.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A really good catch by Jonny Bairstow to end the innings! Length ball, outside off. Yadav goes for the heave but gets the outside edge. Jonny Bairstow moves to his right and takes a sharp catch. India are bowled out for 191!
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: England are underway and Burns is too! Angled into the pads, Burns works it through square leg. Two taken.
Yadav gets it right this time. Brings it back in from around off, defended nicely by Burns though.
Another one on a length and just outside off. Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Another one on a length and just outside off, easy leave.
Outside off, one more harmless ball. Not played at.
A dot to end! A good start by Yadav! On the pads, this is worked to square leg.
Angled in on middle, Hameed works it to sqaure leg.
Outside off, some nice carry for Bumrah. Left alone.
That is a nasty delivery! This lands on a length, pitches, takes off and also holds its line. Hits the glove of Hameed as he tries to defend.
Just outside off, Bumrah is getting it to zip through. Left alone.
Yet another delivery outside off, Hameed lets it be.
One more nut outside off, Hameed does not play at it.
Good length and just outside off, not played at.
Back of a length and on off, Burns stands tall and blocks it.
Three more! Fuller and outside off, Burns drives it through point. Three taken.
Yadav slips this one down the leg side, Hameed looks to flick but misses.
Some away movement for Yadav but the line is outside off, left alone.
Another one which is well outside off, Hameed does not play at it.
Burns played that quite late! Length and on off, Burns looks to defend, he gets his bat down late. It goes off the bottom edge behind the wickets.

OUT! DRAGS IT ON! Jasprit Bumrah provides the perfect start for India! They desperately needed an early strike and have got it. Burns does not learn from his mistake on the previous ball. This is yet again on a length, closer to the off pole, lands and skids through. Burns once again looks to dab it late, it goes off the inside edge and this time onto the stumps.
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Malan is off the mark! Back of a length ball on off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Good length and on off, Hameed defends it onto the ground.
Really well bowled! Shorter and just outside off, Hameed looks to defend initially but then the ball keeps rising, he lets it go.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The openers, who put up a 100-run stand in the previous game are back in the hut. Jasprit Bumrah is on fire. Two wickets in the over and India right back into this one. The extra bounce does the trick. This is shorter and outside off. Hameed looks to cut but due to the extra bounce, it goes off the outside edge and flies to Pant who takes it above his head.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
A touch fuller and closer to the off pole. Malan blocks it from the crease.
Full ball, but wide outside off. Malan leaves this one alone.
Play and a miss! Shorter ball, outside off. Malan misses the cut.
Fuller ball, around off. Malan gets forward and defends it with his bat and pad close together.
Back of a length, around off. Malan hops up and blocks it.
Fuller ball, around off. Root comes forward and blocks it well.
Back of a length, around off. Root stays in the crease and blocks this one out.
Short of a length, outside off. Root guides it with soft hands towards gully. The man gets across to his right and stops the ball.
FOUR! Lovely stroke! Length ball, outside off. Root plays it late and runs it between gully and third slip for a boundary. He will play that shot in his sleep and still score runs.
Length ball, outside off. Root has no qualms in leaving this one.
Shorter ball, outside off. Left alone by Root.
Fuller ball, around off. Malan pushes it to covers.
On a length, around off. Malan looks to block it but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Length ball, around off. Malan presses forward and blocks it well.
A touch fuller, outside off. Malan leaves it alone now.
Fuller ball, on off. Malan is solid in his defence of this one.
Shorter ball, down leg. Malan goes for the pull but does not middle. The ball goes past Pant and they get one.
Yorker, on off. Blocked out by Malan.
Full ball, angling away from the off pole. Malan leaves this one.
Very full again, on off. Malan blocks it back to the bowler.
Length ball, on the pads. Malan flicks it away. Umesh Yadav runs across from fine leg to his right keeps it to two.
FOUR! EDGY! Full ball, outside off. Malan goes for the drive and gets the outside edge. The ball runs past the slip cordon and runs to the fence.
Full ball, on off. Malan blocks it solidly back to the bowler.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Root gets the bat down in time! Full ball, on off. Root stays in his crease and looks to block. He gets his bat down in time and gets the outside edge. The ball bounces on its way to the slip cordon.
Full ball, on leg. Root misses his whip and gets hit on the pads. A soft appeal is put in but the ball is likely sliding down leg.
FOUR! He has hit that one alright! Length ball, on the pads. Root whips it past mid-wicket and gets a boundary.
Shorter ball, outside off. Root works it towards the gully fielder.
FOUR! Cracked away by Root! Short ball, outside off. Root latches onto it and flays it past point for a boundary.

Too high! Even Bumrah appeals late! Angled into the pads, this one skids through. Malan looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but turned down. The replay confirms that the ball was going over the stumps.
Good length and just outside off, Malan plays inside the line and lets it be.
On off, this is pushed to covers for one.
On the fuller side this time, Malan plays it to mid on.
Back of a length and on middle, blocked.
FOUR! Beautiful shot by Malan! It also made a cracking sound as the ball came off the bat! Fuller and outside off, this is creamed through covers. Boundary.
A short one on the body, it is pulled to fine leg for one.
Shorter in length and on off, Malan defends it onto the ground.
Yet another delivery on middle, this lands and then moves away. Malan is a little squared up as he tries to block. Keeps it out in the end though.
FOUR! Nicely played in the end! Shorter and just outside off. Malan plays it late, he opens the face at the very end and guides it past point for a boundary.
Well fielded! Fuller and on off, Malan pushes it towards wide mid off. Bumrah runs to his right, dives and stops it.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
FOUR! Runs flowing now! Shorter and on the pads. Root works it to fine leg, this one races away to the fence. Not the best of starts from Siraj.
Good length and on off, Root plays it late and to point.
Siraj goes wide of the crease and angles it towards the middle pole, blocked.
Back of a length and on off. Root guides it through point, there is now a fielder in the deep so just the one.
FOUR! Yet another poor ball and Malan works it for a boundary. On the pads, Malan hangs back and works it through square leg for a boundary.
A couple of runs now! On the pads, this is worked through square leg for two. 11 from the first over of Siraj.
Two more! Shorter and outside off, Root guides it through point for a couple.
Another single! Short again and outside off, Root guides it past point for one more.
Two more! Another one which is slightly shorter in length and outside off, Malan guides it through gully for a couple. 50 up. Runs flowing now.
Back of a length and on middle, from around the wicket, Malan hangs back and keeps it out.
A little too straight yet again, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Defended nicely! On off, Root hangs back and keeps it out.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone by Malan.
Back of a length, around off. Malan pushes it towards point.
Fuller ball, wide outside off. Malan leans forward and then leaves this one.
Length ball, on the pads. Malan works it towards deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, around off. Root blocks it from the crease.
Another length ball, on off. Root stays in his crease and blocks it with no issues whatsoever.
Length ball, down the leg side. Malan misses the flick.
Fuller ball, on off. Malan blocks it out.
A short ball, outside off. Malan is not bothered with this one.
Short ball, down the leg side. Malan gets inside the line of the ball and leaves it alone.
Three short balls in a row. This is outside off and Malan makes another leave.
Make that another short ball, outside off. You guessed it right, Malan leaves this one too.
Fuller ball, outside off. Root pushes it towards point.
Short of a length, outside off. Root blocks it from the crease.

OUT! BOWLED! Stop the press! Stop the press as India have sent Root back early! Yadav does the job with a snorter of a delivery. He serves a length ball, outside off and gets it to come back in. Root looks to block but the ball goes through the gate and hits the off pole. Yadav is delighted and so he should be! We have seen Root being dismissed quite a few times with the ball which jags back in after pitching. We remember Cummins doing that a couple of times during the Ashes, both in Australia and England. Yadav does something similar here. The key was the ball jagging back in and skidding through.
Howout: b Umesh Yadav

Commentary: Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, around off. Overton looks to block but gets he inside edge towards fine leg for one.
Length ball, on leg. Malan works it towards square leg.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball now, on off. Overton blocks it from the crease.
A bouncer, on off. Overton gets under the ball and lets it sail over his head.
Length ball, on leg. Overton gets hit on the pads while looking to flick.
Back of a length, around off. Overton stays in his crease and blocks it towards the leg side. The last ball of the day coming up.
Overton survives! Yorker, on off. But the tall pacer does well to dig it out. What a day of Test cricket this has been. It is Stumps on Day 1!
Siraj starts with a length ball, around off. Malan defends it out watchfully.
Good-length ball, outside off. The ball is moving away from the left-hander. Malan leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a length, around off. Moving away. Malan prods and shoulders his arms.
This time Siraj serves a full-length ball, on off. Malan works it towards mid on off the inner half.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Malan stays inside the crease and defends it to the leg side.
Maiden to start. On a length, outside off. The ball does not bounce much after pitching. Malan lets it go to the keeper.
Yadav starts with a length ball, around off. Overton hangs back and defends it to cover.
Full-length ball, on off. Overton defends it out watchfully.
BEATEN! Some away movement this time for Yadav. He serves it on a length, outside off. Overton looks to poke it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT! Umesh Yadav gets rid of the night watchman. Overton was enticed by the width in the previous delivery. So, Yadav offered him the width yet again, but this time Overton got punished. A length ball, outside off. Moving away. Overton stays inside the crease and looks to work it to the off side. He only manages to get a thick outside edge. The ball flies towards Virat Kohli at first slip who gulps it down with ease.
Howout: c Virat Kohli b Umesh Yadav

Commentary: Ollie Pope is off the mark straightaway! A length ball, on the pads. Pope tucks it through mid-wicket and takes off for a single.
A length ball, on off. Malan defends it out solidly. A great start for Umesh Yadav.
A length ball, on middle and off. Pope hangs back and defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, outside off. The ball nips in off the pitch. Pope shoulders his arms.
A length ball, around off. Pope blocks it out watchfully.
BEATEN! This was a beauty by Jasprit Bumrah. He serves it on a length, outside off. The ball nips in off the pitch. Pope looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Outside off. Pope leaves it alone.
A full-length ball, on off. Pope defends it out solidly to see off the over. A maiden for Jasprit Bumrah.
FOUR! Nicely played. Malan gets the first boundary on Day 2. A length ball, on the pads. Malan stays back and tucks it through square leg. The ball races away to the boundary.
A length ball, on off. Malan defends it out.
A full-length ball, on off. Malan drives it to mid off, but cannot find the gap.
Good length and outside off. Malan leaves it alone without any hesitation.
On a length, around off. Malan defends it to short cover off the outer half.
Full and on off. Malan stays back and punches it to mid off.
A length ball, on off. Pope blocks it to cover.
Good length and outside off. Pope shoulders his arms.
A length ball, outside off. The ball jags in. Pope is confident about the bounce and he shoulders his arms.
Full length and on off. Pope defends it out solidly.
A touch short, outside off. Pope has no stroke to offer.
A length ball, around off. Pope looks to defend it out but gets an outside edge towards gully.
A full-length ball, just outside off. Malan hangs back and defends it to the off side.
Outside off. Malan is happy to leave it alone.
A length ball, around  off. Malan blocks it out from inside the crease.
A length ball, around the hips. Malan hops and tucks it through square leg for a single.
On a length, around off. Pope stays back and punches it through cover. Mohammed Siraj gives it a chase and cuts it out before the ropes. The batters take three.
Length and on off. Malan defends it out off his front foot.
A length ball. This one comes in from outside off. Pope defends it out watchfully.
On a length, outside off. This one jags in a long way. Pope shoulders his arms. Pant moves to his left to grab the ball.
The first fiddle from Pope. He was not sure about the shot at all. A length ball, outside off. Pope looks to work it to the off side but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
A length ball, around off. The ball jags in and it also gets an extra bounce off the pitch. Pope looks to defend it out but misses. He gets hit near the groin area.
Good length and on off. Pope drives it to the right of mid off. Mohammed Siraj there dives to his right and makes a sharp stop.
A length ball, on off. Pope defends it out watchfully.
Yadav comes around the wicket now. He serves a length ball, around off, moving in. Malan defends it out solidly.
Good-length ball, outside off. The ball nips in a bit. Malan leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT! One more for Umesh Yadav and this one is better as he gets Dawid Malan walking. Yadav gets his third wicket of the game. He serves it on a length, just outside off. Making sure Malan plays at it which he does. Malan looks to poke it out but only manages to get a thick outside edge. The ball goes towards the slip cordon, where Rohit Sharma dives to his right to complete the catch. This is the start that India were looking for.
Howout: c Rohit Sharma b Umesh Yadav

Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow shoulders his arms.
Beauty from Yadav! A length ball, around off. The ball moves in off the pitch. Bairstow looks to defend it out but only manages to get an inside edge onto the pads.

NOT OUT! Jonny Bairstow survives the review. A length ball, around off. This one jags in. Bairstow stays back and looks to defend it out but misses. He gets rapped on his pads. Yadav puts in an appeal but the umpire says no. After a chat with the skipper, Virat Kohli decides to take it upstairs. The UltraEdge shows the bat is absent. The Ball Tracker confirms the ball is missing the wicket. India lose a review here.
A length ball, on off. Pope defends it to cover and rotates the strike.
A length ball, on off. Bairstow defends it out solidly.
On a length, just outside off. Bairstow blocks it to point.
Good length and outside off. Bairstow shoulders his arms.
A length ball, on off. Bairstow hangs back and defends it back to the bowler.
Full-length ball, around off. Bairstow defends it to cover off the front foot.
Touch fuller and on off. Pope hits it past mid off on the rise. Cheteshwar Pujara gives it a chase and cuts it off before the ropes. The batters take three.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! A full-length ball, around off. Moving away a bit. Bairstow punches it past mid off. The ball races away to the boundary this time.
Full length and on off. Bairstow defends it to cover off the outer half. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.
Full and outside off. Bairstow slashes it to point.
On off, kept out.
Good length and outside off. Bairstow leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Bairstow has no stroke to offer.
Good-length ball, angling in from middle. Pope turns it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, outside off. Ollie Pope pushes it to cover off the back foot.
FOUR! STREAKY! Banged in short, around leg. Ollie Pope looks to hook it but gets hit on the gloves before kissing his helmet and the ball goes over the keeper for a boundary to fine leg.
Length ball, coming in from middle. Ollie Pope looks to defend but gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
Good-length ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Short of a length, around the fourth stump. Jonny Bairstow gets behind the line and defends it solidly.
Starts with a length ball, on off. Ollie Pope gets forward to defend this one.
Good-length ball, darted on the pads. Pope turns it to mid-wicket.
Shortens his length this time! Back of a length, on off. Ollie Pope blocks it out.
Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope looks to drive through cover but only gets a thick outside edge towards backward point.
Full ball, angling in late. Ollie Pope pushes it back to the bowler.
Length ball, on the pads. Pope flicks it off his pads towards deep sqaure leg for a couple. Mohammed Siraj chases it and keeps it down to two.
Good-length ball, jagging back in sharply. Jonny Bairstow looks to drive on the up but gets the inner half of the bat towards cover.
Good-length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow cuts it hard but Ravindra Jadeja at backward point dives to his left and stops a certain boundary.
Good-length ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to cover.
Back of a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow works it on the leg side comfortably.
Well bowled! Length ball, around the fourth stump channel. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend but gets an outside edge and the ball rolls towards KL Rahul at third slip.
In the air...but safe! Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow drives it uppishly towards cover. The ball goes wide of the fielder and lands safely.
Thakur starts with a good-length ball, around off. Ollie Pope blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Back of a length, on off. Ollie Pope gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! CLASSY! Full ball, in the slot. Ollie Pope gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it handsomely back past the bowler for a boundary.
FOUR LEG BYES! Good-length ball, strayed on the pads. Ollie Pope misses the flick and the ball clips his pads before racing away for a boundary towards fine leg.
FOUR! AND AGAIN! Length ball, angling in on the pads. Ollie Pope whips it off his pads through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
FOUR! Ollie Pope is on a roll! Short ball, outside off. Pope rocks back and pulls it through square leg for another boundary. 16 runs from the over!
An inswinger, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to mid on.
Half an appeal from Rishabh Pant behind the stumps but the umpire turns it down. Good-length ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow misses the flick and gets hit on the pads.
Length ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow comes forward to flick it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! EDGED AND FOUR! Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend it with soft hands and gets an outside edge back past KL Rahul at third slip for a boundary.

FOUR! Not where Bairstow intended though! Back of a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow looks to whip it on the leg side but gets the inner half of the bat just over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
FOUR! SMASHED! Short and wide. Jonny Bairstow stays back and cuts it hard through cover for yet another boundary.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Ollie Pope flicks it wide of Jasprit Bumrah at mid on and takes a single.
Short ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to pull in front of square but the ball goes straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to drive on the up but he misses as the ball zips past his outside edge.
Short of a length, on off. Jonny Bairstow gets an inside edge onto the pitch as he looks to punch it through cover.
Length ball, angling in from outside off. Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone.
Short and wide, asking to be hit. Jonny Bairstow cuts it towards Ravindra Jadeja at deep point to take a couple of runs.
Lovely delivery! Length ball, jagging back in sharply. Ollie Pope misses the flick and gets rapped on the pads. Umesh Yadav appeals but the umpire is unmoved.
Short ball, outside off. Pope cuts it hard but straight to Ravindra Jadeja at backward point.
A length ball, on the pads. Pope tucks it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! What a shot. Runs are coming in thick and fast for England now. A full-length ball, around middle and off. Bairstow pushes it down the ground. The ball races away to the boundary at log on.
On a length, outside off. Bairstow pushes it to point. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.

FOUR! That's another four. They are just dealing in boundaries at the moment. A length ball, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow hangs back and clips it past the diving fielder at mid-wicket. The ball races away to the boundary. This is the 9th boundary in the last 4 overs.
Good length and outside off. Bairstow looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
A full-length ball, on off. Pope defends it to cover.
Outside off, left alone by Pope.
Good-length ball, on off. Ollie Pope blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope gets forward and drives it to mid off.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope shoulders arms to it.
Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it hard through cover but the fielder at cover dives to his right and saves three runs as he gets a hand to it.
Length ball, around off. Ollie Pope pushes it wide of mid off and collects a run.
FOUR! WOW! Full ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow drives it gloriously through cover and the ball races away for a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it towards point for a single.
Full ball, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it to mid off.
Short of a length, outside off. Ollie Pope taps it behind square on the off side for a single.
Length ball, in the slot. Jonny Bairstow drives it hard back to the bowler.
Short ball, outside off. Ollie Pope cuts it to cover.
Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope looks to drive but inside edges it to mid on.
Good-length ball, on off. Ollie Pope looks to cut but gets an inside edge behind the stumps.
Length ball, on the pads. Ollie Pope flicks it to fine leg for a run.
Short ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow ducks under it comfortably.
On a length, on off. Ollie Pope defends it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Ollie Pope blocks it out.
Flighted ball, on off. Ollie Pope pushes it to mid on and takes a quick single.
Tossed up, outside off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
On a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow defends it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Jonny Bairstow prods and defends it solidly.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope looks to leave it but gets an under edge as the ball rolls away towards the slip cordon.
Length ball, on off. Ollie Pope defends it watchfully.
Short of a length, outside off. Ollie Pope taps it towards point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
FOUR! SHOT! Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope comes forward and drives it through cover for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Ollie Pope looks to leave it late but he gets a bat on it back to Rishabh Pant who dives to his left to stop the ball.
Tossed up, on off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it solidly.
Tossed up, on middle. Jonny Bairstow defends it solidly.

No ball! An appeal for LBW but the umpire turns it down! Flatter ball, on middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow prods to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Tossed up, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Well bowled! Flighted ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow defends it out to cover-point.
Quicker ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards deep square leg for a run.
Good-length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow gets behind the line to block this one out.
Length ball, angling in from middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge towards fine leg for a couple.
Short of a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow defends it off the back foot.
Lovely delivery! Good-length ball, just outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to poke at it but is beaten as the ball whistles past his outside edge.
Bye! Length ball, way down leg stump. Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone and Rishabh Pant fumbles behind the sticks. The batters take one.
Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope lets it through to the keeper.
Tossed up, on off. Jonny Bairstow drives it hard to cover. The umpire signals a no ball as Jadeja oversteps.
Tossed up, on off. Jonny defends it out.
Flatter ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow blocks it watchfully.
Tossed up, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to cover.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Jonny Bairstow stays back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Short ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow cuts it hard but straight to the backward point fielder.
Flatter ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards cover-point and looks to take a run but was rightly sent back by Ollie Pope. It will be LUNCH on Day 2.
Siraj starts with a full-length ball, on off. Pope defends it to mid-wicket off the inner half.
Full length and on off. Pope stays back in the crease and works it towards mid on.
On a length, outside off. Pope slashes it towards deep point. Pujara is placed there. The batters take one.
Length and around off. The ball jags in a bit. Bairstow defends it back to the bowler.
Full length and on off. Bairstow stays back and pushes it towards sweeper cover. The batters pick up two comfortably.
A length ball, on off. Bairstow stays back and watchfully defends it to cover.
Looped up, full and on off. Pope defends it out solidly.
Quicker. Flatter and on the pads. Pope defends it to the leg side.
Floated full and on off. Pope prods and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Pope defends it to cover.
Floated full and outside off. Pope opens the face of the bat and guides it towards third man. The batters pick three before the fielder cuts it off.
On the pads. Bairstow flicks it to mid-wicket.
An inswinger. Full and on middle and leg. Pope stays back and clips it through square leg for a couple now.
A length ball, on off. Pope punches it to cover but straight to the fielder.
Full length and on middle. Pope tucks it to the right of mid on. They take one.
On a length, around off. The ball nips in a bit. Bairstow works it towards mid-wicket off the inner half.
Touch fuller and on off. Bairstow defends it to point off the front foot.
A full-length ball, around middle and off. Bairstow works it towards mid on.
Floated and on off. Pope blocks it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, outside off. Pope skips down the track and keeps it out
On off, blocked out.
Full and on off. Pope defends it out off the front foot.
On the pads. Pope flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full and around off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to cover for a single.
A full-length ball, on off. Bairstow pushes it towards mid on.
A full-length ball, around off. Bairstow looks to defend it out and does so with the outer half towards mid on.
No ball! Full ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to mid off.
Full ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow works it to the leg side.
Length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow prods to defend this one.

OUT! LBW! Mohammed Siraj strikes after Lunch. A much-needed breakthrough for India. Good-length ball, angling in late from middle. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Siraj puts in an appeal and the umpire raises his finger in a flash. Jonny Bairstow is unhappy and decides to take it upstairs. The UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracker shows three reds and Jonny Bairstow has to go back. He is not happy with himself.
Howout: lbw b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Lovely delivery! Good-length ball, outside off. Moeen Ali looks to poke but he misses as the ball zips past his outside edge.

Tossed up, on middle. Ollie Pope defends it to cover.
Flighted ball, on off. Ollie Pope pushes it to cover and collects a run.
FOUR! Flatter ball, turning in from middle and leg. Moeen Ali tickles it towards fine leg to get off the mark. The ball races away for a boundary.
On a length, on middle. Moeen Ali comes forward to block it.
Loopy ball, on off pole. Moeen Ali digs it out watchfully.
Length ball, on off. Ollie Pope defends it to cover.
Full ball, angling in late from middle. Ollie Pope turns it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, on middle. Ollie Pope works it towards mid-wicket.
Siraj serves a length ball, on middle. Ollie Pope pushes it to mid-wicket watchfully. Mohammed Siraj is in the middle of a good spell here.
Well bowled! Length ball, jagging back in from off. Ollie Pope defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, just outside off. Ollie Pope drives it to cover.

Flighted ball, outside off. Moeen Ali defends it watchfully.

FOUR! Flicked away fine and Ollie Pope gets his fifty in some style. A full-length ball, down leg. Pope stays back and flicks it towards fine leg. The ball ends up in the boundary. He has stood up when his team needed him the most. Brilliant knock from him.
A length ball, on off. Pope blocks it out.
Full and on off. Pope pushes it towards mid off.
On a length, outside off. Pope taps it to point and takes off for a single.
Outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Good length and outside off. Ali lets it go to the keeper.
Darted on the pads. Pope tucks it to square leg. The batters take two as the fielder there fumbles.
Full and on off. Pope defends it to short leg.
Flighted full and on off. Pope prods and defends it onto the pitch.
Loopy ball, down leg. Pope stays back and flicks it through square leg. The batters take two.
On off, kept out watchfully.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Pope slashes it through covers for a single.
On a length, outside off. Pope stays back and cuts it square on the off side. They take one.
A short ball, on middle. Ali ducks under it.
On a length, around off. Ali defends it out with soft hands.
A length ball, around middle and off. Ali defends it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
Length and around off. Ali defends it out solidly.
Back of a length and around off. Ali defends it to cover.
A length ball, on off. Pope defends it to cover and takes a single.
FOUR LEG BYES! A touch short, on the bodyline. Ali stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the thigh pad and goes towards fine leg. The ball races away to the boundary.
A full-length ball, on off. Ali keeps it out.
Good-length ball, outside off, moving away. Ali has no stroke to offer.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, Ali defends it out.
A length ball, outside off. Pope leaves it alone for the keeper.
A length ball, on off. Pope stays back and pulls it through square leg for a single.
A length ball, on off. Ali works it towards mid on.
A length ball, on off. Ali pushes it to cover.
Outside off, left alone by Ali.
LEG BYE! A length ball, on the pads. Ali looks to flick it but misses. The ball though clips the pads and rolls out. The batters collect a leg bye.
Good-length ball, angling away with the angle, from middle. Moeen Ali blocks it solidly.

FOUR! STREAKY! Good-length ball, outside off. Moeen Ali looks to poke at it but gets an outside edge. There is a big gap between third slip and gully and to Moeen's luck, the ball finds that gap and races to the third man fence.
BEAUTY! Good-length ball, moving away from off. Moeen Ali looks to defend but gets beaten as the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
Length ball, around off. Moeen Ali square drives it to backward point.
Banged in short, outside off. Moeen Ali sways away from the line of the ball.
Good-length ball, moving away with the angle, around off pole. Moeen Ali comes forward to block this one out.
Length ball, on middle. Ollie Pope gets behind the line and pushes it to mid on.
Short and wide. Ollie Pope stays back to cut this one through backward point to collect a single.
Good-length ball, angling in, from middle. Moeen Ali turns it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Width on offer and Ali pounces on it! Short ball, outside off. Moeen Ali rocks back and cuts it hard through backward point for a boundary.

In the air...but safe! Short ball, down leg. Moeen Ali hooks it towards fine leg. Umesh Yadav puts in a dive to his left and stops a certain boundary. The batters take a couple. Great effort in the deep from the big man and it is applauded by skipper, Virat Kohli.
Good-length ball, on off. Moeen Ali defends it to cover.
Good-length ball, way outside off. Pope shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Pope gets forward to block this one.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope prods to push it to cover.
Length ball, just outside off. Ollie Pope drives it to mid off.
Well bowled! Length ball, angling in late, from outside off. Ollie Pope looks to defend but gets hit high on his bat as there is some extra bounce on offer.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope taps it to cover.
Length ball, on off. Moeen Ali drives it to mid off where KL Rahul dives to his right and stops the ball.
Length ball, around off. Moeen Ali prods to block this one out.
Short of a length, around the fourth stump channel. Moeen Ali blocks it onto the pitch.
Length ball, outside off. Moeen Ali reaches out and square drives it towards Ravindra Jadeja at backward point.
Length ball, coming in with the angle, from off. Moeen Ali gets behind the line and pushes it to mid on.
Length ball, around off. Moeen Ali defends it back to the bowler. Another Maiden over!
Good-length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope taps it towards backward point and collects a single.
Good-length ball, moving away from outside off. Moeen Ali leaves it alone.
Length ball, around off. Moeen Ali defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, jagging back in, from off. Moeen Ali turns it to mid on.
A yorker, around off. Moeen Ali digs it out watchfully to the leg side.
Good-length ball, on off. Moeen Ali pushes it to cover off the back foot.
Good-length ball, on leg. Ollie Pope turns it to mid-wicket and scampers through for a run.
Umesh Yadav sprays a short ball down leg. Moeen Ali misses the flick and the ball goes back to Rishabh Pant behind the sticks.
Short of a length, around off. Moeen Ali taps it to cover.
Good length ball, on middle. Moeen Ali turns it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Glorious! Back of a length, just outside off. Moeen Ali punches it off the back foot through extra cover and the ball races away for a boundary. A left-hander's delight!
Umesh serves a good-length ball, on middle. Moeen Ali defends it off the back foot.
On a length, around off. Ollie Pope defends it to cover.
A tad short, outside off. Ollie Pope cuts it to cover.
Tossed up, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it through cover for a run. England lead by 1 run now!
Flighted ball, on off. Moeen Ali blocks it out.
Flatter ball, outside off, turning in late. Moeen Ali leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, around off. Moeen Ali prods to block this one out.
Good-length ball, angling in, from off. Ollie Pope defends it soldily.
Length ball, around the fourth stump channel. Ollie Pope defends it to cover.
Short of a length, jagging back in, from middle. Ollie Pope turns it to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Length ball, around off. Moeen Ali stays back and flicks it wide of the mid on fielder.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Length ball, around off. Moeen Ali presents the full face of the bat and drives it back past the bowler for a boundary.
4 Leg byes! Umesh bangs in short, around the rib cage. Moeen Ali looks to duck under it but gets hit on the body and the ball rolls away towards fine leg for a boundary.
Tossed up, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it through cover and takes a couple of runs.
Loopy ball, on off. Ollie Pope blocks this one.
Flatter ball, around off. Ollie Pope defends it out.
Tossed up, around off. Pope pushes it to cover.
Flatter ball on middle and leg. Pope clips it to sqaure leg.
Tossed up, outside off. Pope gets low and drives it to cover-point.
On a length, just outside off. Pope stays back and punches it through point for a single.
FOUR! THUMPED! A short ball, on off. Ali stays inside the crease and pulls it through mid-wicket. The ball races away to the boundary.

Tossed up and on off. Pope pushes it to cover for a single.
