Floated full and outside off. Pope slashes it through covers for a single.
Flighted full and outside off. Ali punches it past extra cover. They take one. The lead moves to 24 runs.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! A length ball, outside off. Ali stays back and drives it through cover. The ball races away to the boundary.
On a length, just outside off. Ali pushes it through cover. Jasprit Bumrah runs to his left to keep the ball in. The batters take a couple.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, outside off. Ali looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Ali defends it out solidly.
Full, around middle and off. Ali stays back and blocks it back to the bowler.
A length ball, on the pads. Ali looks to flick it away but does not get the connection he was looking for. The ball goes to the leg side off the outer half.
Floated full and on off. Pope makes room and pushes it through cover for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Moeen Ali gives his wicket away. England change room wouldn't be happy about it. He was getting the runs but went for an unnecessary shot of looking to go big which proved to be a costly one. Ravindra Jadeja gets his first wicket of the game at such a crucial point. Floated full and outside off. Ali strides forward and looks to go big. But he does not middle it. The ball goes miles up in the air towards cover. Rohit Sharma settles under it and does the rest.
Howout: c Rohit Sharma b Ravindra Jadeja

Full-length ball and on off. Pope stays back and pushes it to mid off.

A length ball, on the pads. Woakes flicks it to square leg.
Short ball and on off. Woakes sways away from the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Classy shot from Woakes. Overpitched and just outside off. Woakes leans in and creams it through cover. The ball races away to the boundary.
A length ball, on off. Woakes defends it out with a straight bat. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2.
Bumrah starts with a short-of-a-length ball, around off. Ollie Pope blocks it out.
Good-length ball, darted on the pads. Pope flicks it towards mid-wicket and collects a run.
FOUR! Back of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes stays back and taps it back past Rohit Sharma at second slip for a boundary.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Good-length ball, around off. Woakes opens the face of the bat and runs it down towards third man for another boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Chris Woakes drives it back to the bowler.

Tossed up, on leg. Ollie Pope blocks it out.

Bumrah serves a length ball, on off. Pope blocks it to cover.
Good-length ball, on middle. Ollie Pope works it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, jagging back in sharply, from off. Ollie Pope looks to defend but he misses and gets hit high on the pads. No Ball called by the umpire as Bumrah oversteps.
Good-length ball, around off. Pope gets behind the line to block this one.
Flatter and fuller on off. Woakes blocks it.
Tossed up, on off. Woakes defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on middle. Woakes works it towards mid on.
On a length, around off. Woakes blocks this one out.
No ball called as Jadeja oversteps again. Flighted ball, on off. Woakes pushes it to cover.
Loopy ball, outside off. Woakes drives it through cover and collects a run.
Tossed up, around middle and leg. Pope comes forward and blocks this one solidly.
Length ball, moving away, outside off. Woakes leaves it alone. No ball called by the umpire as Thakur oversteps.
Length ball, outside off. Woakes lets it go through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, moving away late. Woakes shoulders arms to it.
Short of a length, outside off. Woakes offers no stroke to this one.

Length ball, moving away just that little bit. Woakes comes forward but sways away from the line.

In the air...but falls short of the slip fielder. Tossed up, around middle. Pope looks to flick it but gets an outside edge and the ball falls just short of Ajinkya Rahane at first slip.
Flatter ball, on middle and leg. Pope flicks it towards square leg for a run. 250 up for England.
Tossed up, outside leg. Woakes comes forward and pads it away.
On a length, around middle. Woakes blocks it watchfully.
Quicker ball, on middle and leg. Woakes defends it off the front foot.

OUT! Dragged on! A wicket against the run of play! Shardul Thakur strikes as Ollie Pope has thrown away his wicket here! Huge wicket this for India in the context of this game as Pope was well set and marching along nicely. Thakur serves a good-length ball, outside off. Pope looks to guide it through third man but only manages an inside edge and the ball crashes onto the stumps. He is very disappointed with himself as he has to walk back after a hard-fought 81.
Howout: b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: Little but of swing this time. A length ball, on the pads. The ball nips in a bit. Robinson flicks it through square leg for a couple.
A length ball, on off. Robinson pulls it to deep square leg for a couple.
A length ball, on off. Robinson pushes it to cover.
On a length, around off. The ball nips away. Robinson plays it back to the bowler.
A single to end the over. On a length, just outside off. Robinson punches it through point for a run.

OUT! BOWLED! Ravindra Jadeja strikes from the other end now! A tossed up delivery, around middle. Ollie Robinson gets low to slog sweep but he misses it completely as the ball turns away a bit and goes past his blade onto the stumps. Two wickets in quick succession here for India and they are right back in the game.
Howout: b Ravindra Jadeja

Commentary: Flatter ball, on off. James Anderson stays back to block it.
Tossed up, outside off. James Anderson pushes it to cover-point to get off the mark with a single.
Flighted ball, on middle and leg. Woakes steps down and works it down the ground for a run.
Tossed up, around off. James Anderson blocks it off the front foot.
Play and a miss! Tossed up, outside off. James Anderson gets low to reverse sweep but he misses and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Full ball, way outside off. Woakes leaves it alone.
FOUR! SHOT! Good-length ball, outside off. Woakes walks across the pitch and drives it through cover for a boundary.
FOUR! AND AGAIN! Short ball, outside off. Woakes rocks back and pulls it in front of square towards wide long on for a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Woakes guides it towards third man for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. James Anderson gets behind the line and blocks it.
Short of a length, around off. James Anderson stays back to block but he misses as the ball hits him on the body and rolls towards the slip cordon.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Woakes digs it out back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, down leg. Woakes stays back to flick it towards square leg for a run.
Tossed up, outside off. James Anderson looks to poke at it but the ball zips past his outside edge.
A tad short, outside off. James Anderson punches it to cover.
Flighted ball, on off. James Anderson blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Quicker ball, outside off. James Anderson leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off. Woakes drives it to cover.
Umesh spills one down leg. Woakes misses the flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Back of a length, on off. Woakes blocks it off the back foot.
Good-length ball, outside off. Woakes looks to free his arms through the off side but he gets a thick inside edge onto his thigh.
FOUR! Good-length ball, outside off. Woakes drives it through cover for a boundary.
Short of a length, around off. Woakes guides it towards third man and scampers through for a run.
FOUR! A low full toss, on the pads. Woakes flicks it through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
FOUR! SMASHED! Good-length ball, outside off. Woakes makes room and smashes this one through covers for a boundary.
Slower ball, outside off. Woakes taps it towards backward point.
Another slower ball, on a length. Woakes drives it to cover but does not take a single.
FOUR! STREAKY! Banged in short, around middle. Woakes looks to pull but gets a top edge back over the keeper's head for a boundary. Rishabh Pant gives it a chase but the ball wins.
Short ball, outside off. Woakes looks to guide it over the slip cordon but he fails to get any bat on it.
Leg bye! Banged in short, around off. James Anderson looks to defend but he misses and gets hit on the body. The battes sneak in a bye as the ball rolls away towards the off side.
Length ball, outside off. Woakes drives it towards sweeper cover.
Full ball, around middle. Woakes digs it out towards third man.
Play and a miss! Good-length ball, outside off. Woakes swings hard but misses.
Banged in short, around off. Woakes taps it to cover and collects a run this time.
Umesh bangs one short, around middle. James Anderson gets behind the line and blocks it.
A length ball, on off. Woakes pushes it to cover.
Full and outside off. Woakes stays back and reaches out. The ball goes towards third man off the inside edge.
Short ball, on off. Woakes stays back and looks to pull it away but misses.

FOUR! Chris Woakes gets his FIFTY! What a Test match he is having. A full-length ball, on off. Woakes lifts it towards long on. The ball ends up in the boundary. A well deserved half-century for Chris Woakes.
On a length, around off. Woakes plays late at it and guides it towards the slip cordon.

OUT! RUN OUT! And India finally get the last wicket. Short ball, around middle and leg. Woakes looks to scoop it over the keeper but he misses. Woakes is not even in a position to run but Anderson calls him through for the bye. Rishabh Pant collects the ball cleanly behind the sticks and he throws it back to Jasprit Bumrah who catches it and hits the stumps at the non-striker's end. Chris Woakes is well short of his crease and he is run out. England are all out with a lead of 99.
Howout: run out (Rishabh Pant / Jasprit Bumrah)

Commentary: Anderson starts with a length ball, outside off. Sharma leaves it alone.
BEATEN! On a length, outside off. The ball nips away. Sharma stays back and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, on the pads. Sharma tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off. Sharma pushes it to cover for a single.
Back of a length and around off. Rahul defends it out watchfully.
A length ball, on off. Rahul defends it out solidly.
EDGY! A full-length ball, on off. Sharma stays back and looks to flick it away but gets an outside edge. The ball goes towards Moeen Ali at gully. The umpire calls a no ball as the bowler oversteps.
FOUR! STREAKY! Full ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma looks to poke away from the body and gets a thick outside edge through the slip cordon for a boundary.
A length ball, on the pads. Sharma tucks it to square leg for a single.
Length ball, outside off. KL Rahul is beaten past his outside edge as the ball moves away slightly.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, outside off. KL Rahul looks to poke at it but misses.
On a length, outside off. KL Rahul defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! WOW! What a shot! Full ball, outside off. KL Rahul prods and drives it through cover for a boundary.
A length ball, on off. Sharma blocks it out.
On a length, around off. Sharma steers it towards third man.
FOUR! Nicely played. A length ball, on off. Sharma guides it towards third man. The ball races away to the boundary.
A length ball, on the pads. Sharma defends it out.
Full and on off. Sharma pushes it to cover.
On a length and on off. Sharma stays back and defends it out.
Good-length ball, darted on the pads. KL Rahul tucks it towards square leg for a run.
Length ball, moving away slightly, from outside off. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, on off. Rohit Sharma gets behind the line and blocks it watchfully.
Length ball, angling in from middle. Rohit Sharma turns it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma pushes it to mid on.
Full ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma drives it through covers. Haseeb Hameed gives it a chase and saves a run for his side as the batters run three.
Good-length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma blocks it solidly.
Short of a length, around off. Rohit pushes it to cover off the back foot.
Length ball, jagging back in from middle. Rohit pushes it to mid on.
Length ball, around off. Rohit comes forward and drives it to cover.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, angling in late. Rohit looks to defend but gets an inside edge and the ball falls just wide of the stumps.
Short of a length, around off. Rohit Sharma taps it behind square on the off side.
Good-length ball, around off. KL Rahul stays back and taps it towards backward point.
Length ball, angling in late, from middle. KL Rahul prods and defends it out.
Back of a length, around middle. KL Rahul tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off. Rohit pushes it to cover.
Length ball, around middle. Rohit pushes it to mid on off the front foot.
Full ball, on middle and leg. Rohit flicks it towards mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off. Rahul defends it back to the bowler.
A full-length ball, on off. Rahul defends it out to point off the outer half.
FOUR! What a shot! On a length, just outside off. Rahul stays back and punches it through cover for a boundary.
A length ball, on off. Rahul blocks it out solidly.
On a length, outside off. The ball gets an extra bounce off the pitch. Rahul leaves it alone.
A full-length ball, on off. Rahul defends it to the off side.
On a length, around off. Sharma blocks it back to the bowler.
A length ball, around middle. Sharma stays back and tucks it to deep square leg. The batters pick two runs.
On a length, around middle and leg. Sharma hangs back and nudges it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off. Sharma defends it out.
On a length, around off. Sharma punches it to point.
A length ball, on off. Sharma hangs back and defends it out watchfully.
A length ball, straying on the pads. Rahul defends it to the leg side with soft hands.
Back of a length and on off. Rahul punches it through cover off the back foot. The batters take two comfortably.
On a length, around off. Rahul blocks it out.
A length ball, on the bodyline. Rahul stays inside the crease and tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
CLOSE! A full-length ball, on off. Sharma looks to defend it out. The ball bounces off the pitch and goes over the stumps.
On a length, around off. Sharma defends it to the leg side off the inner half.

FOUR! EDGY! On a length, outside off. The ball jags in a long way. Rahul looks to work it on the off side. But manages to get an inside edge. The ball scoots past the stumps and goes into the boundary at fine leg.
Good-length ball, outside off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Rahul leaves it alone. Jonny Bairstow dives to his right to collect the ball.
A length ball, on off. Rahul defends it out solidly.
On a length and outside off. Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
Good length and outside off. The ball nips away off the pitch. Rahul has no stroke to offer.
On a length, around off. Rahul defends it out watchfully.
Full length and on the pads. Sharma stays back and clips it through square leg. The batters take one.
On a length, just outside off. Rahul hangs back and defends it to cover.
On a length, around off. Rahul blocks it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
On a length, just outside off. Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
A length ball, on off. Rahul pushes it to point.
On a length, around off. Rahul stays back and steers it towards the slip cordon.
Good length and outside off. The ball is moving away. Sharma leaves it alone for the keeper.
BEATEN! On a length, just outside off. The ball moves away a bit. Sharma looks to defend it but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
A length ball, on the fourth stump line. Sharma leaves it alone.
Good length and outside off. Sharma has no stroke to offer this time.
On a length, around off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Sharma watches it sail past him.
A length ball, on the pads. Sharma tucks it to mid-wicket for a single. Just a single off the over then. Woakes kept things tight throughout.
A length ball, on off. Sharma pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, around off. Sharma defends it to cover.
A length ball, around off. The ball nips in a bit. Sharma tucks it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! A length ball, just outside off. Rahul stays back and punches it through point. The ball races away to the boundary.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, outside off. Rahul looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, on the pads. Rahul tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off. Sharma blocks it out to the leg side off the inner half.
Full-length ball, on off. Sharma stays inside the crease and blocks it out watchfully.
On a length, around off. Sharma pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball, outside off. Sharma leaves it alone
On a length, outside off. The ball swings away off the pitch. Sharma leaves it alone.
A length ball, on the pads. Rahul tucks it to square leg for a single.
Length, around middle and leg. Sharma stays back and clips it towards square leg for another single.
A length ball, on off. Rahul pushes it to cover.
On a length, outside off. Rahul prods and defends it out watchfully.
A full-length ball, on off. Rahul plays it back to the bowler.
A length ball, around off. The ball nips in and gets some extra bounce off the pitch. Rahul stays back and looks to defend it out, but only manages to get and inside edge onto his body.
Back of a length, on off. Sharma hops and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off. Sharma defends it onto the pitch.
Good length ball, outside off. Sharma leaves it alone.
A length ball, on the pads. Sharma clips it to square leg for a single.
Full and on off. Rahul blocks it out solidly. He has to survive one more ball before Stumps.
Yes he does survive. A length ball, on the pads. Rahul stays back and flicks it towards square leg. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Anderson is right on the money. He serves it in the line of the stumps, around middle and off, Rohit brings down a straight bat in defense.
Pitches it up and just around off, holding its line, Sharma covers his stumps and makes a leave.

Shout for an lbw! The umpire shakes his head. Seemed a bit high. Anderson hurls across a length ball, around off and shaping in, Sharma fails to defend and is hit on the back pad. The appeal is made but to no avail. Too high.
India are away on Day 3. Fuller and close to off, Rohit gets forward to defend but it takes the inner edge and rolls behind square leg. The batsmen cross.
On and around off, a length ball, KL Rahul drops it down with gentle hands to square leg and picks up a single.

FOUR! Glorious, that's the only word to describe this shot. This is slightly overpitched from Anderson, around off, Rohit brings down a straight bat and caresses it past the bowler for a boundary down the ground. This shows that the pitch is still a true one for stroke-making. India trail by exactly 50 runs.
Good line to begin. Full and angling in around off, Rahul is on the front foot as he defends it to the off side.
Smart bowling! Woakes delivers it full and on middle, some movement in the air, Rahul does well to defend it back with a straight blade.
Fullish around middle and leg, Rahul keeps it out safely near the surface.
Slightly short and around middle, Rahul works it down with soft hands to square leg and looks for a run. Sharma sends him back.
Fuller and on off, the batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Back of a length, close to off, Rahul goes on the back foot and plays it down to cover-point. Woakes begins with a maiden.
Anderson releases it quite full and around off, not much movement, Sharma defends it with an angled bat to point.
Pitches it up and around off, Rohit drives it down the ground but finds mid on.
Fullish and on off, angling in, Rohit is forward, plays close to his front pad as he pushes it to mid off.
Some movement from the pitch! It's around off and nips away a bit, Sharma tries to defend but it whistles past the outside edge.
50 up for India! Once again the Indian openers have done a great job. Anderson goes searching for the outswinger from middle and off, Sharma flicks it through square leg for a single.
On a good length outside off, holding its line, Rahul plays inside the line and then withdraws his bat at the last moment.
Fuller and closer to off, moving in, Sharma is forward in defense but he gets an inside edge behind square leg. One run is taken.
Full and angling in, around off, KL defends it back to the bowler.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Fullish and close to off, Rahul gets forward and defends it with an angled bat to cover-point.
Shortish and around off, Rahul moves across and defends it down safely.

FOUR! Fabulous shot! This time KL Rahul plays a straight drive. The length is full and on middle, Rahul shows the full face of his blade and strokes it down the ground for a boundary. It's been a good start for India this morning.
Good length, on middle, Sharma hops and defends it out onto the pitch.
Full on middle, Sharma pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to it.
Good length, outside off, Sharma watches it go past him and into the keeper's gloves.
On a length on off, angling in. Sharma looks to defend but it goes off the inner half to the leg side.
On a good length outside off, Sharma lets it go to the keeper.
Movement but after the ball went past the bat! Good length outside off, Rahul looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it. A good take by Bairstow.
On a length outside off, Rahul leaves it alone. Good leave.
Loose shot from KL Rahul! Shortish ball outside off, Rahul looks to cut but misses.
Fullish ball on off, Rahul opens the face of the bat and guides it to gully.
On off, Rahul pushes it to point.

Good work by Haseeb Hameed! Good length around off, Rahul looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge through gully. Hameed chases after it and he seems to have pulled it back in before the ropes. The umpires refer it upstairs and they deem that it is a fine save. Haseeb saves a run for his side.
Robinson starts with a full delivery on middle, Rahul works it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length around off, Sharma prods and then defends it to covers.
Full outside off, Sharma leaves it alone.
Good length around middle, Sharma clips it to square leg for a single.
Fuller on off, Rahul is solid in defense.
FOUR! Oh, beautiful, absolutely beautiful! Fuller length outside off, Rahul leans forward and drives it through the cover-point region for a boundary. India are 64 for no loss.

Chance missed. Full on the pads, Sharma works it wide of mid on for one. Anderson has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. The replays, later on, show that Rohit would have been a goner in case of a direct hit.
Good length around middle, Rahul blocks it to the leg side.

SIX! That has gone all the way! Rahul was surprised by it but he won't mind as long as the runs come! Short on middle and leg, Rahul looks to pull but it goes off the top edge over fine leg for a biggie.

NOT OUT! Wickets missing and a loud cheer goes off around the ground! Excellent review. Rahul was reluctant to take the review but he took it and it paid dividends. Woakes runs in and bowls an inswinger on middle and leg, Rahul looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Woakes and England appeal and up goes the finger. Rahul consults his partner on whether to take the review or not. He is not too confident but he takes it. The UltraEdge shows no bat while the Ball Tracker shows that it would have missed the stumps.
Full outside off, Rahul looks to drive but fails to get any bat on it. KL seems to be a bit rattled and needs to regain his composure.
Full and on middle, Rahul defends it to mid off. End of an eventful over.
Good length around middle, Sharma nudges it to mid-wicket.
On a length on off, Sharma solidly blocks it to covers.
On a length outside off, Sharma has no problems in leaving it alone.
EDGED! Fuller length outside off, Sharma looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge through the gully region. Hameed chases after it and cleans it up but cannot stop the batters from taking two.
On off, Sharma defends it out.
Good length around middle and leg, Sharma looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but the umpire shows no interest.

A stifled appeal from an lbw! Not given. No DRS taken. Woakes brings a length ball into the batsman from outside off, Rahul tries to defend late but misses and is hit high on the back leg. Too high again.
Back of a length, around off, some extra bounce, KL goes back and defend it late down towards point.
Edged but safe! Fullish and on middle, straightening a bit, Rahul is a bit across in his stance as he tries to deal with it. The ball takes the outer edge and rolls to the slip cordon.
Woakes throws a tempter outside off, wide outside off and there to be chased but KL is watchful as he allows it through.
Nicely angled in, on a length and close to off, Rahul allows it to come to him and then jams it down near his front pad.
Woakes goes fuller and delivers it around off, Rahul uses his wrists this time and tickles it behind square leg for a single.
Angling in from a length around off, Rahul is on his toes as he defends it down on the surface.
Serves it on a length and around off, KL defends it by opening the face of his bat. The ball rolls to point.
Angling into the batsman, on middle and leg, Rahul helps it off his pads to mid-wicket.
This one is served on a driving length outside off, Rahul takes his front leg forward and decides not to offer any shot.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, Rahul eases it towards long leg and picks up a single.

DROPPED! Not easy but one more catch has been put down by Rory Burns. Could not snaffle it. Robinson dishes it out on a fuller length outside off, Rohit goes after it needlessly as he looks to drive but the ball takes a thick outside edge. Burns dives across to his right from the second slip region, gets a touch on it but fails to pouch it. The ball travels behind and the batters take two.
On middle and leg, defended from the crease to the on side.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Short and wide outside off, left alone.
Back of a length, on top of off, Rahul goes back and taps it down to backward point.
Beauty! Woakes is bowling some great balls here. Delivers it on a length, close to off and it moves away late, Rahul tries to defend but is beaten all ends up.
Pitches it up and around off, Rahul presses forward and pushes it to the cover region.
On a length, around off, Rohit hangs back and uses the angle of the bowler to keep it out on the leg side.
Fuller and on off, Sharma is forward as he pushes it gently to wide mid off.
In the channel outside off, on a length, Sharma lands his front leg forward to cover the line and then shoulders arms.
A touch short and in the zone outside off again, Sharma offers no shot.
Lovely placement. Rohit Sharma leans into a fuller delivery and strokes it through extra cover. He collects a couple of runs.
Extra bounce this time. On a length around off, jagging back in, Sharma tries to defend but misses and is hit high on the pads.
Shortish and on off, Rahul hops on the back foot and punches it to mid off.
Lands it on a good length, around off and angling in, Rahul sits back inside the crease and defends it late towards point.
Shortish again, around off, Rahul goes back and pushes it towards the bowler. Not from the middle of the blade though.
Slight inward movement, from a length around off, Rahul uses his wrists and turns it down towards fine leg for one.
A bit short again, around off, Sharma gets back to work it on the leg side but it takes the inner half, strikes him on the thigh pad and rolls back to the bowler.
In the channel outside off, an easy leave for Rohit Sharma.
Full outside off, Rahul drives it wide of mid off where the fielder makes a good stop. Keeps it down to a run.
Full on off, Sharma defends it out onto the pitch.
Full on middle, Sharma looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge to the cover-point region for one.
An inswinger on middle, Rahul goes back in his crease and then defends it back to the bowler.
Good length outside off, Rahul chops it to point.
Full and outside off, Rahul makes a leave to the keeper.
Back of a length, on off, Sharma blocks it to covers off the back foot.
Outside off, left alone by Sharma.
Full ball on off, Sharma prods and blocks it to covers.
Anderson goes full again on off, Sharma attempts to defend this but it goes off the outside edge to gully.
BEATEN! This is superb from Anderson! He has to bowl there more often! Good length and outside off, Sharma hangs his bat out in defense and it beats the edge by a whisker.
Back of a length on off, Sharma defends it to point.
Good length on off, angling in, Rahul defends it to cover.

Full in length and around off, Rahul brings down his bat in defense but the ball straightens a bit to takes the outer edge. It races past gully. The deep point fielder shuffles across to his left to collect the ball and the batsmen take a run.
Fuller on off, Sharma pushes it to mid off.
Good length around middle, Sharma flicks but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
On a length around middle, Sharma solidly blocks it out.
Full on off, Sharma gets behind the line of the delivery and then defends it to mid off.
Back of a length outside off, Rahul punches it to cover.
Good length around off, angling in, Rahul defends it late towards gully.
Good length and outside off, Rahul puts his bat behind his pads and lets it go to the keeper. Jonny Bairstow fails to collect it cleanly but no chance of a run.
Fuller on off, Rahul defends it out to covers.
Finds the fielder! Short and wide outside off, Rahul cuts it towards backward point. A good diving stop by Ollie Pope.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! There is a spike as the ball passed the bat and Rahul goes for 46. England were pretty confident that they had got their man and they have! Very good delivery from James Anderson and he has reaped the rewards. Good length around off, Rahul looks to defend but he seems to have gotten an edge as the ball straightens from there. Bairstow catches it and England start celebrating. But the umpire is unmoved. They take the review. The UltraEdge rolls in and it shows a spike. Rahul is not happy as he walks off. Maybe, he feels that the noise might have been from the bat hitting the back pad. KL gestures the same to the umpires as well. But if you watch the replays, the spike came when the bat was near the front pad and at that time, there was a good gap. India trail by 16 runs.
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b James Anderson

Commentary: Full on middle, Sharma drives it back towards the bowler. It hits the stumps at the other end. No harm done.
Another full one on middle, Sharma pushes it to mid on.
Fuller on off, Sharma pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length on middle, Sharma nudges it to mid-wicket.
Good length outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to it.
Serves it on a length and wide outside off, Pujara shoulders arms.
Anderson drops it on a good length again, outside off, Pujara leaves it. There is some late movement when it goes past the batsman.
Jimmy continues to test Pujara with a delivery in the corridor of uncertainty. The Indian number 3 is quite certain that he has to leave it.

Pujara is off the mark in a nervy manner. Sudden change in length from Anderson, he goes fuller and around off, Pujara tries to defend but it takes the inside edge and races down to fine leg. They cross for a single.
Pitches it up and around off, Sharma is forward as he drives it to mid off.
Solid. On a length and close to off, Sharma brings his bat down as he stays inside the crease in defense.
Fullish and on off, Pujara defends it awkwardly with an angled bat towards point.
In the zone outside off, quite away from the stumps, an easy leave for Pujara.
Fuller and closer to off, Pujara gets behind the line and defends it with a dead bat.
Around off on a length, the batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
The line is outside off, Pujara keeps his bat close to his body and makes a leave.
FOUR! Drives it and drives it well. Robinson goes fuller this time, outside off, Pujara gets on the front foot and drives it through the vacant mid off region for a boundary. India trail by 11 runs.
Angling in, from a length around off, Sharma defends it back from the crease.

Catch it is the shout...Doesn't carry! Anderson pitches it up and around middle, Sharma plays it early and chips his attempted on drive. Chris Woakes is stationed at mid on and he picks it very late. His initial movement was to his right and then he has to adjust and dive to his left. The ball though still would not have carried. It runs behind and the batters get two. Root is seen gesturing that it swerved in the air also.
Shortish and on off, punched off the back foot to covers.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Uppish but safe! Anderson gets a full ball to curl back into the batsman, around middle, Sharma tries to flick but it takes the inner half, brushes his pads and doesn't carry to square leg.
FOUR! Shot! Anderson over-pitches this time, around off, Rohit crunches his drive through the gap at covers. The outfield is lightning quick and it beats Haseeb Hameed to the fence.
Overton begins his spell with a full ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms.
Identical to the last delivery, again Pujara covers the line and leaves it alone.
Overton sticks to his line outside off, Pujara also sticks to his plan and leaves. Some late movement there.
Craig tries to get close to the off stump but it's not close enough. Pujara allows it through safely.

FOUR! Pujara is trying to be positive. If it's there, he will play his shots. Short and wide outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara camps back and slaps it through backward point. The deficit is just one run now.
Fuller and around off, Cheteshwar is forward in his defense.
Some turn there. Tossed up around off, a bit short and around off, Sharma gets back and punches it towards the bowler.

ROHIT IS SAFE! Moeen cuts down his length and delivers it fuller this time. It lands outside off and spins back in, Sharma takes his front leg forward and pads it away. They appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Joe Root has a word with his boys and takes the DRS. The Ball Tracker shows that it's missing the off stump. Didn't turn enough.
Presses forward to a full ball and uses his bat this time to defend. Better from Rohit.
On middle, it's worked with the spin towards mid-wicket for a single. All levelled now.
Drags his length short, around off, Pujara goes back to pull but finds the diving mid-wicket fielder.
FOUR! Pujara has nailed it. India are in the lead now. Moeen again bowls it short and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara uses the depth of his crease and rockets his pull shot to square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Put away! Overton tries to test the batsman with a short ball, serves it on middle but it sits up at a good height for the batsman, Rohit rocks back and pulls it well through square leg for a boundary.
Good length on off, Sharma defends it out.
On middle, Sharma pushes it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball on middle, Sharma nudges it to mid-wicket.
Good length around middle, Sharma tucks it to square leg.
Floated outside off, Pujara dances down the track and drives it to mid off where Anderson makes a fine stop.
Loopy ball on middle, Pujara nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball outside off, Pujara goes back and then pushes it to covers for one.
BEATEN! Good delivery! Floated ball outside off, Sharma looks to defend as he plays it for the turn but the ball goes straight on and beats the outside edge.
On off, pushed to the off side.
A dot ball to end the session! Floated on middle, Sharma defends it back to the bowler. LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Fuller in length around off, Pujara is forward with a straight bat in defense.
This one is served a shade behind a fuller length, around off, Pujara goes back and taps it down to covers. Looks for a run but it's not on.
Pujara is very strong on his pads. Overton serves full and around middle, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it through square leg and collects a couple of runs.
On middle, a length ball, Pujara flicks but finds the fielder standing in front of square leg.
Hurls across a gentle inswinger outside off, on a length again, Pujara takes his front leg forward before making a leave.
Back of a length, around off, Pujara stays back and turns it to mid-wicket. A huge shout of no follows.
Woakes starts a fresh spell with a fuller delivery, some movement in the air, Sharma drives it on the up but finds the mid off fielder. No Ball given by the third umpire.
Goes fuller and this time the line is more around middle and off, Rohit shows the full face of the bat and drives it to mid on.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

Appeal for a caught behind! Not given. Excellent line and length. A touch full and around off, moving away a bit, Sharma tries to play straight but it whistles past the outside edge. There is some sound, Woakes turns and enquires but the umpire shakes his head. The replays show that his bat clipped the pads.
Fuller and on off, Sharma uses the angle of the bowler and pushes it to mid on.
Fullish and on off, Sharma is solid in his defense.
Around off, on a length, Sharma is forward as he blocks it with an angled bat to cover-point.
Back of a length, around middle, Pujara hangs on the back foot and glides it wide of gully. Haseeb Hameed chases it down and only a single is taken.
Full and on off, Sharma prods and defends it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, solidly defended out.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma works it to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Cut away superbly! Good length ball outside off, Pujara cuts it through the point region for a boundary. Pujara was running and he seems to have twisted his ankle.
Good length ball on off, Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma works it wide of mid on for one.
On a length on off, Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge to the leg side. Pujara wants the run but is sent back by Rohit.
Full on off, Pujara defends it to cover.
On off, Pujara plays it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to it.
On a length on middle, Pujara nudges it to mid-wicket.
Full ball outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on off, Sharma blocks it to cover.

FIFTY FOR ROHIT SHARMA! It has been an excellent knock from the Indian opener but he would know that his job is only half done and he needs to continue. Good length ball outside off, Sharma punches it through point for a couple.
Outside off, left alone by Rohit.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma works it to mid-wicket.
Full on middle, defended out.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara cuts it to point where Hameed makes a good stop.
Full on off, Pujara drives it wide of mid off where the fielder fumbles. Sharma wants a single and is halfway down the pitch but Pujara is already past the stumps. Sharma is not happy.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
FOUR! What a shot from Rohit Sharma! Brilliant! Full outside off, Sharma leans and creams it through extra cover for a boundary.
On off, kept out.
Good length ball on off, Sharma defends it to mid off.
FOUR! Pujara has played the cut really well today so far! Good length ball outside off, Pujara cuts it through the point region for a boundary.
Full on middle, Pujara works it to mid on.
FOUR! That's clever control from Pujara! Good length ball outside off, Pujara opens the face of the bat and then guides it through gully for a boundary. 50-run stand comes up between these two.
Full on middle, Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
Full on the pads, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, Pujara lets it go.
Full on middle, Sharma works it to mid-wicket.
Full down the leg side, Rohit looks to flick but misses.
Short ball on middle, pulled to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! How well has Pujara played that? He did this in Leeds as well. Short ball outside off, Pujara upper cuts it over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Good length ball around off, Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads.
That's loose from Pujara! Good length ball outside off, Pujara looks to cut but misses.
Floated on middle, Rohit plays it to square leg.
Tossed up on off, Sharma dances down the track and looks to flick but it goes off the leading edge to point.
Flighted ball outside off, Sharma drives it to deep cover for a single.
Floated ball outside off, Pujara pads it away.
Flighted on off, Pujara uses his feet and then works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball outside off, Pujara punches it to deep cover for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Good length ball on the pads, Sharma flicks it to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Sharma defends it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma clips it to mid-wicket.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Too high maybe! Good length ball around off, Sharma looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. England appeal but the umpire is not interested. England do not take the review.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full on middle, Sharma pushes it uppishly but falls short of the mid on fielder.
Tossed up on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball outside off, Pujara punches it to deep cover for a single.
Full on middle, Sharma nudges it down to long on for a single.
Shortish ball outside off, Pujara punches it through extra cover for a couple.
Floated on off, Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Pujara dances down the track and then pads it away.
Good length ball around middle and leg, Sharma looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Fullish ball on middle, tucked to the leg side.
Good length ball on off, Sharma defends it to cover.
Full on middle, defended to mid-wicket.
Full on middle, Sharma drives it back to the bowler and it hits the stumps at the other end.
EDGED AND FOUR! India won't mind these runs! Good length ball around off, Sharma looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and flies to fine leg for a boundary.
Floated on off, Pujara works it to square leg for one.
Short ball outside off, Sharma punches it to deep cover for a single.
Very full on off, Pujara uses his feet and then plays it to mid off.
Tossed up on off, Pujara dances down the track and then drives it to mid off.
On off, defended out.
Loopy ball on middle, CP uses his feet and then works it to mid-wicket.
Full ball outside off, Sharma drives it to deep cover for one.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara defends it to mid on.
On off, kept out.
Full on middle, Pujara pushes it to mid on.
On a length on off, Pujara defends it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara defends it out.
Flatter on off, Sharma punches it down to long on for one.
Tossed up on middle, Pujara dances down the track and flicks it to deep square leg for one.
Full outside off, Sharma drives it to deep cover for a single.
Shortish ball outside off, Pujara punches it to deep cover for one.
Full on off, Sharma defends it out onto the pitch.
Cleverly played! Flatter ball outside off, Sharma waits for it and then guides it through third man for a couple of runs.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara works it to square leg.
Full on off, Cheteshwar defends it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara defends it to the leg side.
On middle, Pujara defends it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on middle, Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
Fullish ball on the pads, whipped to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Sharma is solid in defense.
Fullish ball on off, Sharma defends it to point off the front foot.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma works it to mid-wicket.
Full on off, RS pushes it to cover.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled! Good length ball outside off, Sharma looks to defend but misses.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma works it to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter on off, Sharma defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Excellent shot from Rohit Sharma! Tossed up outside off, Sharma dances down the track and then lifts it over extra cover for a boundary.
Flatter on the pads, tucked to square leg.
Shorter outside off, Sharma punches it to deep cover for one.
Loopy ball on off, Pujara defends it out.
Floated on off, Pujara dances down the track and then works it to mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma defends it to mid on.
Full on middle, Sharma looks to drive but it goes off the inside edge to the leg side for a couple. 3000 runs in Tests for Rohit Sharma.
Good length ball on off, Sharma defends it to cover.
On middle, blocked out.
Fullish ball on middle, Sharma defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma stands tall and then defends it to mid on.
Floated on middle, Pujara flicks it to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! That has found the gap! Tossed up on middle, Sharma goes down on his knees and sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Loopy ball on middle, Sharma uses his feet and then works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Excellent batting! Tossed up on off, Sharma goes on his knees and then paddles it to fine leg for a boundary.
Flatter on middle, Sharma plays it back to the bowler.
This is good batting! Good length ball on off, Pujara guides it to third man for three.
Full on off, Sharma defends it out.
Fullish ball on middle, RS works it down to mid on.
Short ball on middle, Sharma pulls it to deep square leg for a couple. 100-run partnership comes up. Sharma moves to 90.
FOUR! No fielder there and it results into a boundary! Short ball on off, Sharma pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full ball outside off, Sharma leaves it alone.
Tossed up on middle, Pujara nudges it to square leg.
Tossed up on off, CP pushes it to mid off.

NOT OUT! No bat and England lose a review! Tossed up on off, Pujara dances down the track and then looks to defend. However, it takes his pads and lobs to silly point. England appeal for a bat-pad catch but the umpire says no. England take the review. The UltraEdge shows no bat and the Ball Tracker shows the impact to be outside off and the wickets missing. Pujara is safe on both counts and England lose a review.
On middle, tucked to the leg side for one.

SIX! What a way to reach his first Test century away from home! Terrific knock and he will be pleased. The Indian camp is up in applause. Loopy ball on off, Sharma dances down the track and then powers it over long on for a biggie. Just a raise of the bat and he soaks in the applause. This has been some knock. His transformation as a Test opener has been simply amazing. There were doubts about his temperament when opening the innings, especially outside Asia but his knocks in Australia and now here in England have answered many critics. The Hitman would be aiming for a big daddy hundred here.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, Pujara blocks it out.
Good length ball on off, Cheteshwar blocks it to the off side.
On a length on middle, Pujara is solid in defense.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara guides it to short third man.
Full on off, Pujara defends it to cover.
Flatter on middle, Rohit tucks it to mid-wicket.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Tossed up outside off, Sharma pads it away. England appeal but the umpire says no.
Floated on middle, Sharma defends it to mid on.
Flatter on middle, Sharma tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Floated on middle, Pujara uses his feet and then works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball outside off, Pujara pads it away.
Full on middle, Sharma clips it to mid-wicket.
Full down the leg side, Sharma looks to flick but misses.
On a length on off, Sharma defends it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma nudges it to mid-wicket.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Flatter on off, Pujara punches it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Pujara defends it back to Ali.
Floated outside off, Pujara uses his feet and pads it away.
Shortish ball on middle, Pujara works it to deep square leg for one.
Floated on off, Sharma looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full on off, Sharma works it to long on for one.
On a length on middle, Sharma works it to deep square leg for one. India now lead by 100.
Woakes angles it in, a touch fuller, Pujara defends it from the crease to mid-wicket.
On middle and leg, Pujara wrists it across the line but finds square leg.
Too full and around off, Pujara decides to play in the V but finds the mid on fielder.
Change in pace from Woakes but his line is down the leg side, Pujara tries his best to flick but misses.
Solid as a rock! A touch short and on off, Pujara is firmly behind the line with a straight blade as he defends it down. TEA ON DAY 3!
Overton begins his spell from 'round the wicket and digs in a short ball around leg, Sharma rolls his wrists over the ball as he goes for the pull and sends it behind square leg for a single.
Same plan for Pujara. Digs in a bouncer around leg, Pujara ducks.
Back of a length around middle and leg, some extra bounce, Pujara fails to work it around and is hit on the thigh pad.
Fractionally short and around middle and off, angling away, Cheteshwar stays back and taps it down to cover-point.
Shortish and around middle and leg, Pujara stays back and wrists it behind square leg for one.
Catch is the shout, nothing doing. Short again, on middle, Sharma hangs back and plays a controlled pull shot over square leg. Another run to end the over.
Starts with a delivery angling in around off, Sharma gets behind the line and pushes it back to the bowler.
This one is very full and on off, Rohit drives it back and Woakes collects it to his left.
Keeps his line around off and operates on a fuller length, Sharma is forward as he pushes it down to mid off.
A touch short and on off, Sharma stays back and uses the angle of the bowler to help it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, a good off drive from Rohit but it's not in the gap. The Hitman is looking at ease.
On a good length and around off, Rohit plays it late from the crease and guides it towards backward point.
Overton bangs it in short, from 'round the wicket, Pujara ducks and evades it easily.

FOUR! Fifty for Cheteshwar Pujara! Back of a length, around off and angling away, Pujara sticks on the back foot and just uses the pace of the bowler to guide it behind backward point for a boundary. Found some form in Leeds and has just extended it here at The Oval. Can Pujara end his drought and find a century this time?
Shortish and around leg, tickled on the leg side but straight to the fielder at backward square leg.
A touch short and on middle, Pujara moves back and works it towards the fielder on the leg side, this time in front of square leg.
Fractionally short again, on middle, Pujara sits back and plays it down with soft hands to mid-wicket.
Overton continues to bowl short and around middle, Pujara pulls it this time but finds Root at backward square leg.
Serves it on a length and around off, Rohit stays on the back foot and punches it down to mid off.
Slightly short and around off, not much pace there, Rohit moves back and glances it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Woakes delivers it on a good length around off, Sharma strokes it from the back foot to mid off.

FOUR! Easy pickings! Something Root does always. Woakes delivers it on a length and outside off, Sharma waits and just glides it away late down to third man for a boundary. The only slip fielder moves a bit wide now.
Fuller this time, around off, Rohit drives off the front foot to mid off.

Presses forward to a full ball on off and works it off his pads to the leg side. Easy going for India at the moment with nothing much happening from the pitch. This stand has moved to 129 runs and India lead by 113.

Appeal for a caught behind! Nothing from the umpire. Overton goes short and around leg, Pujara tries to pull but misses. It goes closely past his gloves to the keeper. Jonny Bairstow collects and looks to jump first in appeal. He then holds himself back and appeals. Overton is not interested in appealing at all. No gloves, the UltraEdge also confirms.
On middle and leg, worked on the leg side but straight to the fielder at square leg.
Shortish and around off, Pujara plays it with the angle and places it to the right of the gully fielder for a single.
Bouncer around leg, Rohit ducks.

This is smart batting! Sharma anticipates the line to be around leg and hence steps back to make room. He then strokes it wide of mid off and it races away. Overton himself gives the chase and puts in a slide near the fence to pull it back. Saves one run. Full marks to Craig's commitment.
Pujara is not holding back. Short around leg, he pulls but finds Root at backward square leg.
Flatter one, on the pads, helped to square leg.
Shortish and on middle, Rohit goes back and works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy delivery, full and around off, Pujara defends it back.
Root drags his length short and delivers it on off, Pujara pulls but finds the square leg fielder.
Tossed up and on middle, Pujara gets forward and flicks but finds mid-wicket this time.
Quicker and flatter, on the pads, Pujara clips it across the line but again the square leg fielder is there to stop a run.
Shortish and outside off, Rohit moves back and punches it to long on for a single.
A little short and outside off, turning in, Pujara goes back and cuts it to deep cover for a run.
Short again, outside off, Rohit delays his shot and places his cut shot wide of backward point. Picks up a couple. Elegant.
Presses forward to a full ball and defends it to the off side.
Floated one, wide outside off and spinning in a bit, Sharma makes a leave.
Too full and on off, Rohit gets forward and knocks it down to long on for an easy run. India lead by 123.
Floated one, full and around leg, Sharma works it off his pads to square leg.
Quicker and fuller on leg, defended on the leg side.
Fullish and on middle, flicked on the leg side but straight to square leg again.
Tossed up on middle, Sharma leans a bit and helps it with gentle hands to square leg.
Fuller and on middle, Rohit lifts his back leg a bit as he flicks it through the gap at mid-wicket for a run.
Fullish and around leg, Pujara hurries down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Loopy and full around off, Rohit lunges and defends it with his bat and pad together. This one spun a bit.
Flighted and full outside off, this time it has been pushed to covers.
Tossed up, around off and spinning in, Rohit goes back and nudges it to the right side of the square leg umpire for a single.
Flatter and on off,Pujara gets back and defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy and full around off, Pujara leans forward and wrists it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Fine shot! Too full in length and around off, Pujara steps down the track and drills his drive through mid off for a boundary. The stand moves to 145 runs and India lead by 129.
Wayward delivery, full and down the leg side, further spinning away, Sharma leaves and Bairstow stretches to his left to collect it.
FOUR! Thumped down the ground. Tossed up ball, landing full and around leg, Sharma makes room and strokes it elegantly through mid off.
Quicker and around leg, Rohit defends it down from the back foot.
Slightly quicker and fuller on off, Sharma defends it carefully to the off side.
Floated one, full and around middle, it's driven through covers for a run. The 150-run stand comes up.
Tossed up and around off, Pujara defends it from the front foot to the leg side.
Spinning in from around off, Sharma moves back, allows it to come to him and then nurdles it to square leg for a single.
Walks down the pitch to a full ball and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Again Pujara uses his feet to a full ball but this time finds mid on with his on drive.
Loopy and full around off, Pujara skips down the track and works it wide of mid-wicket. Screams 'wait' as the fielder from the deep is charging towards the ball.
Flatter and shorter on middle, Pujara immediately goes back and tucks it to deep square leg for a couple.
Quicker one, flatter and wider outside off, Pujara allows it through. England have finished the last few overs in the blink of an eye.

OUT! Rohit holes out, once again while attempting a pull shot. Ollie Robinson delivers it short and around off, it has not bounced much and has come off the surface slowly. Rohit aims for the pull shot but is way too early into the shot. The ball kisses the top edge and flies to fine leg. Chris Woakes moves across to his left and makes no mistake in the deep. England have a wicket out of nowhere. Sharma would be devastated with this tame dismissal. End of a century stand and a magnificent knock by the Hitman. A wicket immediately with the second new ball and the hosts have an opening. Can they capitalize? The lead is 137 runs.
Howout: c Chris Woakes b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Delivers it on a length and angles it down the leg side, Kohli tries to flick but misses. Jonny Bairstow collects and appeals but nothing from the umpire.
In the channel outside off, on a length, Kohli allows it through to the keeper.
Full and around middle, angling in, Kohli closes the face of his bat and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Virat is off the mark in a tricky manner. An in-dipper from Robinson, on a length close to off, Kohli tries to defend but it takes the inner edge and runs down to fine leg for a run.

OUT! The new ball has brought two breakthroughs for England and Ollie Robinson is flying in celebration. Ollie delivers it on a shortish length and gets it to jag back in sharply. Pujara is caught on the back foot as he tries to defend by going on his toes. There seems to be an inside edge and the ball deflects off the back thigh pad to third slip. Moeen Ali collects the ball and the hosts appeal vociferously. The umpire remains still. England are very sure and take the DRS. The UltraEdge detects a spike and India have lost their third wicket. The momentum is shifting in this Test match again with both the set batsmen dismissed in no time.
Howout: c Moeen Ali b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: On a length around off, defended to covers.
Appeal for a caught behind! Back of a length, outside off and holding its line, some extra bounce too, Kohli pushes inside the line and misses.
Fuller and on off, Kohli gets forward, opens the face of the bat slightly and defends it to covers.
In the zone outside off, Kohli shoulders arms.
Extra bounce on this one, on a length and outside off, Kohli leaves and it thuds on his back thigh. Big movement.
Pitches it up and around off, Kohli pushes it with gentle hands to mid off.
On and around off, angling away, Jadeja pushes it defensively towards point for a brisk run.
In the region outside off, on a length, Kohli allows it through.
Fuller and on off, angling in, Kohli pushes it to cover-point.
Too full and on off, Kohli leans forward and across before flicking it to mid on.
On a length around off, Kohli presses forward with an angled bat and eases it down to third man. Haseeb Hameed chases it down and the batters collect three.
FOUR! Streaky! Fuller in length, outside off and angling away, Jadeja looks to drive through the line but edges it wide of backward point for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off, Kohli has nothing to do with it.
Anderson gets closer to the off stump line, serves it full, an outswinger, Virat defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish and on off, Kohli uses his wrists and pushes it down to mid on.
On and around off, a length ball, Kohli plays late and taps it down to point.
In the channel outside off, an easy leave for the Indian skipper.
Anderson bends his back and digs it short around off, Kohli gets on top of the bounce and plays it down to point.
Delivers it on a length around middle and off, Jadeja stays back and defends it to cover-point.
Fuller and closer to off, Jadeja gets behind the line and pushes it back to the bowler.
Keeps it close to off, on a length, Jadeja gets half-forward and defends it to the off side.
Fuller and on middle, Jadeja tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Pitches it up and around off, Jadeja gets forward and pushes it defensively to mid off.
fuller and on off, Jadeja offers a straight bat as he defends it back. Two maidens in a row.

Full and around off, Kohli looks to defend but it takes the inner edge and rolls behind square leg for a single. The throw comes to the keeper who gets a bad bounce and fails to collect. Kohli looks for the second run but then decides against it.
Back of a length around leg, Jadeja tries to glance but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.
Brilliant line from Anderson. He angles it away from the southpaw, on a length, Jadeja stays back to cover his stumps and offers no shot.
Identical to the last delivery, again Jadeja makes a watchful leave.

Appeal for a caught behind! The finger stays down. There was some noise. On a length around middle and off, Jadeja looks to defend but misses. It sneaks past him to the keeper and Bairstow appeals after collecting the ball. Maybe it kissed the flap of the front pad. Root opts not to take the review as Anderson was unsure.
On a length around off, defended from the crease to covers.
In the right channel outside off, the batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Full and on off, Kohli gets forward and pushes it with an angled bat to point.
A touch short and around off, Virat shoulders arms.

FOUR! Nicely played! Robinson delivers it on a length close to off, Kohli plays late and opens the face of his bat to guide it past the slip cordon. Rory Burns gives the chase from second slip, puts in a slide near the fence and pulls it back. The umpire gets it checked upstairs and the replays show that his left knee touched the cushion when he was in contact with the ball.

Howzzat? Robinson goes wide of the crease and angles it in on a length around middle, Kohli tries to flick but misses. He is hit high on the pads, they appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Too high. England have only one review left, so Root is also being careful here.
FOUR! Class of Virat Kohli. Robinson pitches it up and around off, Virat Kohli leans into the drive and crunches it through the gap at covers. India lead by 155 runs.
On a good length, outside off and angling away, Jadeja allows it through to the keeper.
Beats the outside edge! Anderson takes a length ball away from the left-hander, the angle does Jadeja in, as he feels for it and misses.
Back of a length, around off, Jadeja stands tall and plays it down to cover-point.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja makes an easy leave.
On a length, around middle and off, Jadeja defends it back to the bowler.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump. A pretty harmless over from Jimmy.
A touch short and outside off, Kohli stands across in his crease to guard his stumps as he makes a leave.
Angling in from a length around off, Kohli lets it come to him and then blocks it on the leg side.
Full in length on middle and leg, served from wide of the crease, Kohli fails to flick and it goes off his pads to fine leg. The bowler appeals and the batters cross. Given as a leg bye.
Fullish and on off, Jadeja draws forward and defends it from the inner half of his blade.
On a good length around middle, Jadeja closes the face of his bat and helps it to mid-wicket.
Hits the deck hard and lands it on a good length around off, Jadeja is solidly behind the line in defense.
Slightly short and on off, Virat stays back and once again allows the ball to come to him. He then plays it late and taps it down to backward point.
FOUR! Elegance! Anderson bowls it full and around off, Kohli leans forward and unveils a lovely square drive for a boundary. The lead is now 160 runs.
On a length and outside off, some extra bounce, Kohli shoulders arms.
Aims the off stump with a length ball, Kohli gets forward and defends it to the off side. Gentle hands.
Hurls across a delivery in the channel outside off, Kohli finds it to be too wide and makes a leave.

FOUR! Kohli is oozing class at the moment! Anderson serves a half-volley, it's around off, once again Kohli leans forward and transfers his weight into the shot. Doesn't try to hit it hard, just times it through the gap at covers for a glorious boundary.
Flatter ball outside off, Jadeja cuts it to point.
Loopy ball outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Tossed up on off, Jadeja defends it to covers.
Looped up ball outside the off stump, Jadeja makes a leave to the keeper. Big spin on this one.
Floated on middle, Jadeja looks to defend but gets an inside edge to short leg.
Full on middle, Jadeja looks to defend again but inside-edges it to the leg side. Bairstow appeals, thinking that it is pad first but the umpire turns it down.
Flatter ball outside off, Kohli punches it to point for one.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Shortish on the pads, Jadeja places it through the square leg region for a boundary.
Flatter ball on the pads, Jadeja looks to flick but it goes off the pads to fine leg. Two leg byes taken.
Full on off, Jadeja defends it to covers.
Tossed up on off, Jadeja watchfully defends it to the cover region.
Flighted ball outside off, Jadeja gets forward and pushes it to covers again.
Serves a length ball, on off. Kohli prods forward to defend and does it off the inner half of his bat to square leg.
On a length, outside off. Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Slightly shorter, outside off. Kohli hops and taps it to point.
Way outside off, on a length. Kohli lets it through to the keeper.
A length ball, angling on the pads, this is flicked through square leg for a single.
A touch fuller, on the pads. Jadeja tucks it to square leg.
Short in length, outside off. Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Three runs taken! A full ball, on middle. Kohli flicks it through short mid-wicket. The fielder chases it back and stops it. Three runs taken.
On a length, on off. Jadeja blocks it to point.
A length ball, slanting across, outside off. Jadeja looks to poke it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short of a length, around off. Jadeja sways away from it.
Quick single! On middle, on a length. Jadeja hangs back and nudges it to short mid-wicket for a quick single.
A length ball, on off. Jadeja looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge through the gully region. The fielder does well to stop it near the ropes. Two runs taken.
BEATEN! On a length, outside off. Jadeja looks to defend on the front foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A length ball, outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, on off. Jadeja blocks it on the off side.
A length ball, on the pads, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
On a length, on middle. Jadeja blocks it back to the bowler.
A length ball, outside off, hint of away shape. Kohli offers no shot.
Touch fuller, on off. Kohli takes a big stride forward and defends it to point for a quick single.
Outside off, on a length. Jadeja watchfully lets it through.
This one shapes away off the deck, outside off. Jadeja leaves it alone.
A length ball, on off. Jadeja gets inside the line and blocks it out solidly.
Just around the 4th stump line. Jadeja watchfully lets it through to the keeper.
This one shapes back in from way outside off. Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Another wayward delivery, on a length. Left alone.
Angles it on middle, on a length. Kohli leans and flicks it wide of deep square leg. The fielder runs across and cuts it off. Two taken.
A length ball, outside off. Kohli shoulders arms to it.
A full ball, outside off. Kohli pushes it to covers.
Again serves a full ball, on off. Kohli gets on the front foot and pushes it to covers.
A full ball, angling across, outside off. Jadeja lets it through.
Hurls a full ball, shaping away from the left-hander, outside off. Left alone.
Again a full ball, outside off. Jadeja leaves it alone.
Another full ball, slanting across, outside off. Left alone.
A short ball, outside leg, Ravindra Jadeja just takes his eyes off the ball and takes it on his left shoulder. Does not show any pain but that would have stung.
On a length, on off. Kept out.
Shorter and on off. Kohli defends it to point.
Short in length, on off. Kohli solidly blocks it on the surface.
Touch short, on off. Kohli gets on the front foot and blocks it on the off side.
BEATEN! A length ball, outside off, it and shapes away. Kohli looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
This one was around off, on a length. Kohli prods to defend but gets a thick outside edge through the slip cordon. The fielder chases it back, dives and does well to save a single for his team.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Robinson angles it on the pads. Jadeja hangs back and flicks it to fine leg for a boundary.
A full ball, on middle. Kohli flicks it nicely but finds short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Gorgeous shot! A full ball, outside off. Kohli leans and drives it nicely through covers for a boundary.
On middle, on a length, tucked on the leg side.
Short in length, on off. Kohli waits for the ball and dabs it late to backward point.
A length ball, on off, it lands and nips back in. Kohli hangs back and blocks it on the leg side.
On a length, on middle, pushed to mid on.
Comes around the wicket and serves a length ball, outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, outside off. Jadeja opens his bat face and guides it to the second slip who fumbles. An easy single.
Falls short of the third slip fielder! A full ball, outside off. Kohli gets forward to defend but gets a thick outside edge to third slip who collects it on a bounce.
A length ball, on off. Blocked back on the deck.
Again falls short but this time to second slip! A length ball, outside off. Kohli leans to defend but gets an outside edge to Rory Burns at second slip. The ball bounces in front of him.
FOUR! Bread-and-butter stuff for Kohli! A full ball, on off. Kohli pushes it with gentle hands and the ball races away to the long off fence.
A full ball, outside off. Jadeja defends it off the front foot.

OUT! LBW! Chris Woakes strikes in his very first over of the day! England get the much-needed breakthrough! A length ball, on off, lands and straightens up off the deck. Ravindra Jadeja strides forward to defend but gets hit on the pads. England appeal and up goes the finger. Jadeja has a chat with his captain and goes for the review. No bat involved. Ball Tracker shows three reds and that is the end of Jadeja's innings.
Howout: lbw b Chris Woakes

Commentary: A length ball, on off. Rahane solidly blocks it.
A length ball way outside off. Rahane shoulders arms to it.

NOT OUT! Wickets missing! Good review from India. A length ball, around off, it nipped back in. Ajinkya Rahane shouldered arms and the ball struck him on the front pad. There was an appeal for LBW and up went the umpire's finger. Rahane had a look at Kohli and seemed to suggest that height could be an issue. They took the review and sure enough, Ball Tracker showed the ball to be going over the stumps!
A full ball, on middle. Rahane flicks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on middle. Kohli leans forward and defends it out.
Touch fuller, on off. Kohli prods forward and blocks it out on the leg side.
Very full, on off. Kohli gets on the front foot and defends it to covers.
Touch short, outside off. Kohli watchfully leaves it.
On a length, on off. Kohli pushes it to covers.
A length ball, on off. Kohli gets inside the line and drives it straight to mid off.
On middle, on a length, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on middle. Ajinkya Rahane pushes it under his eyes to mid on.
On middle, on a length. Blocked out.

OUT! LBW! Chris Woakes was surely pumped up and he backed himself against Rahane. No need to review this time for Rahane as it looked plumb with the naked eye. A full ball, swinging in from around off. Ajinkya Rahane looks to flick on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal led by Woakes and the umpire raises his finger. Rahane has a chat with his fellow skipper but opts not to take the review and he continues his walk back to the pavilion. A string of low scores from Rahane.
Howout: lbw b Chris Woakes

Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Pant gets a thick outside edge as he looks to push. The ball rolls through the gully region and they collect a brace. He is off the mark.
Way outside off, on a length. Left alone.
A full ball, on middle, pushed to mid off.
A full ball, on off. Kohli leans and flicks it firmly but finds short mid-wicket.
A length ball, outside off. Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Angles it on middle, on a length. Kohli blocks it out.
A length ball, outside off. Kohli offers no shot.
This was on a length, on middle. Kohli defends it solidly.
On off, kept out.
Full ball outside off, Pant lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Pant shoulders arms to it.
Full on middle, Pant defends it back to the bowler.
Slower ball on off, Pant defends it out.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball, outside off. Kohli lets it through.
On middle, Kohli blocks it on the leg side.
A length ball, outside off. Kohli looks to defend but gets an outside edge to to the first slip. Joe Root there catches it on a bounce.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
Another length ball, on off, Kohli taps it to point for a quick single.
On a length, on middle. Kohli blocks solidly.
Around off, on a length. Pant punches it to mid off for a quick single.
Way outside off, on a length. Left alone.
Serves it on a length, on off, tapped to covers.
Hurls a full ball, on off. Kohli leans and drives it to mid off.
This time pushes to the other side of the bowler as Kohli pushes it to mid on.
Angles a full ball, on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
A slower ball, on middle. Pant defends it back on the surface.
On the pads, this is flicked through square leg for a single.
A full ball, on middle. Kohli pushes it to mid on. He wanted a single but denied in the end.
FOUR! Welcome boundary! A full ball, outside off. Virat Kohli leans into his drive and creams it through covers for a boundary. No need to chase those ones.
A length ball, outside off. Kohli leaves it alone.
A length ball, on middle. Kohli blocks it back on the surface.
Very full, on middle. Pant nudges it to square leg.
A length ball, on off, a slower ball. Pant waits for the ball and defends it on the off side.
Short in length, outside off. Left alone.
Length on off. Pant defends it off the inner half back to the bowler.
Full and way outside off. Pant offers no shot.
A length ball, on off. Pant defends it softly to covers and takes a quick single.
Spills it way down the leg side. Pant misses his flick.
This one skids through on middle. Pant punches off the back foot to covers.

OVERTHROWS! SIX RUNS IN TOTAL! On middle. Pant comes down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket. The fielder from the deep has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. There was no back up and the ball runs away to the cover fence.
A flatter ball, on middle, drilled down to long on for a single.
A loopy ball, on middle. Blocked out.

OUT! TAKEN! Huge wicket for England as they have got the big fish! Ali tosses this outside off, it lands and holds it line. Virat Kohli takes a big stride forward to defend but gets a thick outside edge to first slip. Craig Overton there takes a very good low catch. The change from Root to bring a spinner works brilliantly.
Howout: c Craig Overton b Moeen Ali

Commentary: Length outside off. Pant shoulders arms.
On a length, on middle. Pant solidly blocks it.
Touch fuller, on middle. Pant hangs back and blocks it out.
Short in length, on middle, tucked to square leg.
A length ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Another short ball, outside off. Pant offers no shot.
A full ball, on middle. Thakur jams it out to covers for a single.
A flatter ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Darted on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Thakur defends it on the off side.
Again serves a full ball, on off. Thakur pushes it to covers.
A loopy ball, on off. Thakur prods and defends it out.
On a length, on off. Pant stands tall and blocks it on the off side.
Pant is looking calmer and composed in this innings! A length ball, on middle. Defended out.
Touch short, on middle. Pant defends off the back foot back to the bowler.
A length ball, on middle, pulled away to mid-wicket.
A length ball, outside off. Pant looks to defend away from the body but gets a thick outside edge all along the ground to the slip cordon.
Length outside off. Pant lets it through.
Very full, on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Again serves it full, on middle. Thakur pushes it back to the bowler.
Hurls a full ball, outside off, driven to point.

NOT OUT! A full ball, on off, it lands and spins back in. Thakur looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. The ball lobs and goes to Haseeb Hameed at short leg. There are appeals for both, LBW and catch but neither is given. There is not much conviction but suddenly Joe Root takes the review. There is no need for UltraEdge as the bat is well away from the ball, which has hit the pad and gone to short leg. Now, the third umpire checks for Ball Tracker and it shows the ball to be spinning down the leg side. Wonder who pressed Root into that review. Pressure of the target already?
A full ball, on off. Defended out.
A flatter ball, on off. Thakur knocks it to covers and they take a quick single.
LEG BYE! Short in length, angling on the pads. Thakur misses his flick and gets hit on the pads, They take a leg bye off the pads as the ball rolls on  the leg side.
On the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
A length ball, on off. Thakur dabs it late to gully.
Short of a length, outside off. Thakur punches it to mid off.
On a length, on middle. Thakur pushes it to mid on. He wanted a quick single but was sent back.
Leg bye! Angles a full ball, on the pads. Thakur misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls on the leg side.
On middle, drilled down to long on for a single.
A flatter ball, on middle. Pant advances down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
A loopy ball, on off. Pant solidly blocks it.
Very full, outside off. Pant drives it through covers for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! Moeen pitches it up, outside off. Shardul Thakur drives it uppishly over covers for a boundary.
A flatter ball, quicker and outside off. Shardul Thakur looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, on middle. Pant hangs back and knocks it on the off side.
Full on middle, this is flicked to the leg side for an easy single.
FOUR! Straight drive! A full ball, on middle. Shardul Thakur pushes it nicely wide of mid on for a boundary. Proper cricketing shot.
Around off, on a length, pushed to covers.
Angles it on the pads. Thakur misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
A length ball, way outside off. Shardul Thakur shoulders arms to it. That will be LUNCH on Day 4.
Flatter ball on middle, Pant works it wide of deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Shorter and outside off, Pant punches it through cover for one.
Loopy ball on off, Thakur pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up outside off, Thakur looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge to third man for a couple.
