NOT OUT! Thakur is in! Tossed up on off, Thakur defends it to cover and wants a run but is sent back by Pant. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end and hits. The third umpire is called for and the replays show that Thakur is in. An overthrow taken as the ball goes to deep square leg.
On middle, Pant uses his feet and then works it down to long on for a single.
Punched away! Short ball outside off, Pant punches it through cover and picks up three.
Good length ball on middle, Thakur defends it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Thakur pokes at it but fails to get any bat on it.
FOUR! Thrashed! Full outside off, Thakur whacks it through cover for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Thakur drives it to mid off for a single.
Full outside off, Pant lets it go to the keeper.
Loopy ball on middle, Thakur works it down to long on for one.
Flatter ball outside off, Pant punches it to point.
Floated on off, Pant defends it to cover.
Shortish outside off, Pant plays it to deep cover for a single.
Full on off, Thakur pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Thakur looks to push at it but gets an inside edge to short leg.
Quick run! Full on middle, Pant pushes it to mid on and calls Thakur for the quick single. Makes it easily.
Full ball on off, Thakur defends it to cover.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball on the pads, Shardul clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Fullish ball on off, Pant defends it to point.
Full on off, Pant defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter on middle, Thakur pushes it back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, Thakur drives it to deep cover for a single.
Full on off, Pant blocks it out.
FOUR! Straight down the ground! Tossed up on middle, Pant dances down the track and then lifts it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
On the pads, Pant flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! What a shot that is! Flatter ball outside off, Thakur drives it through extra cover for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Pant punches it to cover.
Full on off, Pant pushes it to mid off and takes a quick single.
Good length ball on off, Thakur defends it to cover.
Back of a length ball on off, Thakur drops his wrists and defends it out.
Full on middle, Thakur drives it back to the bowler.
Finds the gap! Full outside off, Thakur drives it wide of extra cover and picks up two.
Full on middle, Pant works it to square leg.
Good length ball on the pads, RP flicks it to deep square leg for a single. This brings up the 50-run stand between Thakur and Pant.
Full on middle, Thakur flicks it wide of mid on for a single.
Full outside off, Pant drives it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Pant tucks it to mid-wicket.
On off, blocked out.
Full ball on off, Thakur drives it to short cover.
How good a shot is that! Good length ball on middle, Thakur works it through mid-wicket for three.
Full on middle, Pant defends it back to the bowler.
Full on the pads, Pant looks to flick but it goes off the pads to the leg side. An appeal is made for LBW but the umpire says no.
FOUR! Fantastic shot from Pant! Good length ball outside off, Pant cuts it through point for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, RP defends it to cover.
Full on middle, Thakur works it wide of mid on for one.
Good length ball on middle, Pant defends it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, Pant works it to mid-wicket.
Full on middle, blocked out.
Good length ball on off, Pant looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads.
Good length ball on off, Pant defends it to mid off for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Pant pushes it to cover.
Full outside off, Pant leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Pant cuts but finds Hameed at point.
Full on off, Pant defends it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Pant shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, left alone.
Full on off, Thakur drives it to mid off.
Magnificent shot! Back-of-a-length ball outside off, Thakur pushes it through cover-point for three runs.
Back-of-a-length ball on middle, Pant defends it out onto the pitch.
Good length ball on off, Pant defends it to cover.
Full outside off, Pant makes a leave to the keeper.
Full on off, Pant defends it to cover.
Good length ball on off, Thakur defends it to cover.
Full on middle, Thakur nudges it to mid-wicket.
Short ball on off, Thakur pulls it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Thakur defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Thakur pushes it to mid off.
Slower short ball on middle, worked to square leg.
Good length ball outside off, Pant shoulders arms to it.
Full on off, Pant defends it to cover.
Good length ball on off, Pant looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge to first slip.
Good length ball outside off, Pant makes a leave to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Full on off, Pant pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Thakur works it to mid-wicket.
Short ball outside off, Shardul cuts it to deep point for one.

A run out chance missed! What are you doing, England? A golden opportunity to get Rishabh Pant out has gone abegging. Good length ball on middle, Pant works it to mid-wicket and takes off for a single but Thakur is not interested. There is miscommunication again and Pant is sent back. Moeen Ali collects and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. The fielder from square leg backs up but he fumbles too. That allows Pant to make it back in.
On off, Pant pushes it to long off for one.
On off, kept out.
Short ball on middle, Thakur pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Thakur defends it out.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Short ball on middle, Thakur pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Thakur defends it to cover.
Shortish outside off, punched to deep point for a single.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Full around off, Pant goes for the reverse sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. Anderson puts up an appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. England have no reviews left.
Good length ball on off, Pant defends it to point.
SIX! Thakur has picked the bones out of that! Full on middle, Thakur hammers it over long on for a biggie. Moves to 49.
LEG BYE! Good length ball on the pads, Thakur looks to flick but it goes off the pads to the leg side for a leg bye.
EDGED AND FOUR! Runs are coming thick and fast! Good length ball around off, Pant looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge past the stumps and to fine leg for a boundary.
Full on off, Pant pushes it to mid off for a single.

FIFTY FOR SHARDUL THAKUR! Terrific innings from Thakur! He has put India in a commanding position and he deserves all the applause. Short ball on middle, Thakur pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Full on off, Pant defends it to mid off.
FOUR! The lead now moves over 300! What a shot this is! Full and on off, Thakur drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Thakur defends it to deep point for one.
FOUR! India have decided to unleash now! Full outside off, Pant dances down the track and creams it through cover for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Pant defends it to cover.
Full outside off, driven to cover.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on off, Thakur defends it to point for one.
Full on middle, Pant pushes it to mid on.
On a length on off, Pant blocks it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Pant cuts it to deep point for a single.
Full on off, Thakur defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Bang! India motoring now! Full on off, Thakur drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Floated ball on off, Pant looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge to point.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up outside off, Pant drives it to deep cover for one. This brings up the 100-run stand.
Loopy ball outside off, driven to cover.

OUT! CAUGHT AT FIRST SLIP! At long last, a wicket for England! Root has struck and it brings an end to a brilliant partnership. This has put India well on top here. Tossed up outside off, Thakur looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge to first slip where Craig Overton takes it. That is 7 down now.
Howout: c Craig Overton b Joe Root

Commentary: Tossed up on off, Yadav defends it to cover.
FIFTY FOR RISHABH PANT! He is back in form which is a good sign for India! Full outside off, Pant drives it to deep cover for one.
Floated on off, Yadav plays it to long on for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Fifty and out for Rishabh Pant and he is furious with that shot. Tossed up on off, Pant dances down the track and looks to lift it over the bowler's head but mistimes it back to the bowler, Moeen Ali, who makes no mistake. Fine knock by Pant though, who did not play a rash shot till he got settled. In fact, don't remember whether he even played a rash shot at all in this innings. India are now 8 down and they lead by 315. One suspects it is enough and ideally, they should declare now, with around 25 minutes to Tea, to give the English openers some jitters before the break. Nope, they continue to bat on as out comes number 10.
Howout: c & b Moeen Ali

Commentary: Tossed up on middle, Bumrah defends it out.
Full outside off, Bumrah pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Bumrah defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball outside off, Yadav pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Umesh drives it to mid off for one.
Tossed up outside off, Bumrah pushes it to cover.
Flatter ball on off, Bumrah defends it out.
Outside off, driven to cover.
Floated on off, Bumrah is solid in defense.
Tossed up on middle, Umesh works it to mid-wicket.
SIX! Bang! Tossed up outside off, Yadav powers it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie.
Loopy ball on off, Yadav defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Yadav looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge to third man for one.
On off, pushed to the off side for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Yadav works it down to long on for one.
Flatter ball outside off, Yadav slaps it to deep cover for one.
FOUR! Swept away by Bumrah! Tossed up on off, Bumrah sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Bumrah defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball outside off, Bumrah pushes it to cover for one.
Flatter ball on the pads, Yadav tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Quicker ball on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Yadav drives it to long on for one.
Flatter ball outside off, Bumrah guides it through third man for two.
Floated ball outside off, Bumrah defends it out.
Looped up ball outside off, Bumrah lifts it to deep cover for one.
Flatter ball on off, Umesh defends it to cover.
Full on middle, Yadav defends it back to the bowler.
Full on off, Bumrah pushes it to cover and he wants the single but is sent back by Yadav. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
On off, pushed to mid off.
Low full toss on middle, Bumrah plays it to mid on.
FOUR! Superb! That is just class from Bumrah! Full on off, Bumrah drives it through mid off for a boundary.

NOT OUT! It has hit the boot, but then onto the ground! A bit of a drama at The Oval. A tossed up delivery on off, Hameed got a big stride to defend and the ball went to silly point. Now, to the naked eye, it seemed like a normal forward defense. But Jadeja got excited and got the umpires to refer it upstairs, certain that the ball hit the boot and then went to silly point. The umpires got together and referred it upstairs, with the soft signal as not out. And yes, replays confirm that the ball hit the bat, then the boot for sure, but then onto the ground and later, into the hands of the fielder at silly point. The on-field decision stays.

EDGED AND FOUR! Uffff! Why is there that gap between the keeper and second slip? You normally see this from Kohli, when he removes his second slip and pushes his first slip fielder a bit wide. That creates a gap between the keeper and that wide first slip. And more often than not, the ball goes right through that gap. It does so here again. FOUR! Well played! After that previous boundary, Kohli had stationed a leg slip and moved his fine leg squarer. The intention was to bowl a full ball, angling on the pads. NOT OUT! Drama in the fag end of the day. A length ball, angling around middle and off. Hameed leaned and looked to defend but got beaten on the inside edge and got hit high on the pads. Siraj appealed for LBW but it was not given. Now, Siraj was confident as usual and looked at his skipper for the review. His captain turned towards his slip cordon. He asked Pant, Suryakumar Yadav, Rahane and even Rahul. None of them looked even remotely confident and Surya even shook his head. 'AAGE AAKE KHELA WOH?' asked Kohli. Meaning, 'Did he lunge and play?' Kohli was seemingly indicating that because of that lunge, the ball might have hit him low on the pads. Contrary to everyone's suggestions, Kohli went for the review, purely on his gut instinct. However, Ball Tracker showed the ball to be going over the leg stump. Cannot blame Kohli totally here, one could imagine that lunge from Hameed might have tempted him to think that the ball will hit the wickets. Review lost by India.

Gary Pratt, Gary Pratt, howzzat? This is for all cricketing fans. How many of you remember Gary Pratt? He never played a game for England but is remembered fondly by many fans of the Ashes and England. Of course, bitterly by Australia as well. The then Aussie captain, Ricky Ponting, had raised the usage of substitutes on the cricketing field and got angered and irritated when Pratt fired a throw from cover to catch Ponting short at the bowler's end, during the 2005 Ashes. Something similar could have happened here. Full, around off, Rory Burns came forward and then went back to play it to the leg side. Now, as is the flow of momentum, Burns went out of the crease and at that very moment, Suryakumar Yadav, the substitute, standing at short leg, stopped the ball to his left. He immediately transferred the ball to his right hand and fired a throw at the striker's end. He missed and every Indian player on the field had his hands over his head. Was Burns caught napping? He does get two overthrows as the ball goes to fine leg. No sir. Replays show that even if Yadav had hit the stumps, Burns would have been home. Surya reacted swiftly but so did Burns as he did not commit the cardinal sin of committing way too much into the run. So he was able to stop and turn back and get his bat back in the crease, before the ball could hit the stumps. Fantastic cricket at the end of the day, giving us more drama!

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! 50 and out for Rory Burns. Perfect line and perfect length from Thakur. He did his job with the bat in both the innings and we do know he has a knack for picking up crucial wickets. And he is the one to make inroads early on Day 5. Gets a wicket in his first over itself. Thakur bowls a good-length ball, angling in from round the wicket, around off. Rory Burns has a poke at it. The ball kisses the outside edge and carries through to the keeper where Rishabh Pant takes an easy catch. Shardul Thakur draws first blood.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Shardul Thakur

Flighted delivery, on off. Malan uses his feet and nudges it to mid on for a quick single.
Tossed up, on middle. Hameed drives it straight to mid on.

DROPPED! Tossed up again, on off stump. Hameed looks to clear mid on but flat-bats it straight to Mohammed Siraj, who fails to pouch an easy chance. How costly this is going to prove? Siraj seems to have got hurt in the groin region as well. That should have been taken. Ravindra Jadeja is not happy with that.
Flatter one, on off stump. Hameed taps it on the off side. A no ball is called for overstepping.
Floated it up, on off stump. Hameed drives it through covers for a run.
Good-length ball, outside off. Hameed defends it to point.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Hameed shoulders arms.
Length ball, angling on the pads. Hameed works it towards deep mid-wicket and races back for the second.
Full and straight. Hameed gets it off the inside half of the bat to short mid-wicket.
Length ball, on middle. Haseeb Hameed blocks it out.
Right on the money from Shardul Thakur. Length again, on top of off. Hameed stays solid in defense.
Tossed up, outside off. Malan drives it past silly point and gets a single.
Floated it up, on middle. Hameed with a forward defense. Another No ball signaled by the umpire as Jadeja has overstepped.
Flatter one, on off and kept out by Hameed.
Tossed up, around off. Hameed drives it towards cover.
Tossed up again, on off. Hameed puts out a stride to defend it.
Full and on off, Hameed pushes it to mid off for one.

SAFE! Malan gets back in time. Tossed up again and driven to mid on by Malan. The batsmen look for the single but there is a collision between Hameed and Jadeja at the bowler's end and Maln has to go back. There is a direct hit at the striker's end but Malan was in.
Length ball, outside off. The ball stays a little low. Hameed shoulders arms.
On a length, around off. Hameed taps it to point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Hameed lets it sail through.
Length ball on middle, Hameed blocks it out.
Good-length ball, outside off. Hameed watches the ball closely and lets it go.
On a length on off, Hameed taps it to point.

Loopy ball outside off, Malan pads it away. There is a loud shout for an LBW but the umpire shakes his head. The ball hit the front pad first and then the back pad. Virat Kohli opts for a review. Ball Tracking shows umpire's call on wickets hitting and Dawid Malan survives.
On middle and leg, Malan blocks it out.
Full and outside off, Malan is solid in his defense.
Flatter ball on off, Malan pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter and quicker around off, Malan watchfully blocks it out.
Outside off, Malan pads it away.
A full toss on off, Hameed flicks it but straight to short mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, outside off, angling in. Hameed leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Back of a length, on off. Hameed meets the ball right under his eyes.
On a length, on off. Hameed taps it to gully.
Length ball on off, Hameed clips it to deep square leg for a run.
Length ball, outside off. Malan lets it sail through. Just a single from the over.

OUT! RUN OUT! A slight mix-up between Hameed and Malan! Jadeja bowls a flatter ball on middle, Hameed taps it in front of cover-point. He takes off for a quick single. Malan hesitates at first but sees Hameed already charging for a run and he tries to get to the other end as well. The substitute fielder, Mayank Agarwal quickly collects the ball and fires a throw to the keeper where Rishabh Pant whips the bails off in a flash. Umpire takes it upstairs and the replay shows that Dawid Malan is short of his crease despite his full-stretched dive. The Indian fans make a roar and England lose their second wicket.
Howout: run out (sub Mayank Agarwal / Rishabh Pant)

Commentary: Flighted delivery, on leg stump. Root defends it off the back foot.
Fuller one, on the pads. Root gets off the mark with a sweep down to deep backward square leg.
Looped up, around leg stump. Hameed leans forward to defend it.
Fired in on the pads and Hameed clips it past short leg.
Flighted delivery, on the pads again. Hameed stays solid in defense.
Good-length ball, outside off, angling in. Joe Root looks to dab but is cut in half as the ball zips past the inside edge.
On a length on off, Root defends it on the leg side off the back foot.
On the pads, Root clips it to square leg for a single.
On a length around off, Hameed taps it to the man at first slip.
Touch fuller, on middle. Hameed clips it to deep square leg for one.
On off, Root dabs it to the fielder at second slip.
Full and on off. Hameed leans forward and gets it off the outside half of the bat towards point.
Flatter one, on leg stump again. Hameed looks to defend but gets it in the air off the pads. The ball lands safely on the leg side.
Floated it up, on the rough outside leg stump. Hameed pads it away.
Tossed up delivery, attacking the leg stump. Hameed blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on leg again. Hameed pats it back to Jadeja.
Flatter one, on off stump. Hameed punches it off the back foot on the off side.
Good-length ball, around off. Root taps it back onto the deck.
Length ball, angling in on the pads. Root works it off the back foot to deep square leg for one.
A bouncer this time, on off stump. Hameed ducks under it well.
On a good length, around off and nipping back in. Hameed looks to block but misses it onto the back pad. A bit too high.
Length again, outside off and left alone by Hameed.
Fuller delivery, around off. Hameed digs it out to short cover.
Pitched up, outside off and Root drives it nicely through covers. Rahane gives it a chase and keeps it to three.
Good-length ball, on middle. Hameed dabs it down to short mid-wicket.
Fuller delivery, angling in on middle. Well kept out by Hameed.
Full again and on off. Hameed clips it to deep square leg for one.
Yadav is attacking the pads and keeping it full. This one is full and straight. Root pushes it to mid on.
CLOSE! Now Yadav pulls back his length and serves an outswinger around off stump. Root tries to have a poke at it but gets beaten. A No Ball is called for overstepping.
Full again, on off. Root flicks it to deep square leg and will retain the strike.
A bouncer, angled in on the helmet. Root does well to get his head out of the way in time.
Length ball, on off. Root dabs it to cover-point and gets the quick single.
Back of a length, on off. Hameed defends it to short mid-wicket.
Short ball, angling down leg. Hameed ducks under it.
Length ball, on off and kept out on the off side by Haseeb Hameed.
Siraj ends with a fuller delivery, outside off. Hameed is happy to leave the last ball before lunch.
FOUR! Jadeja starts with a full toss on leg stump. Root attacks it straightaway with a reverse sweep into the vacant backward point boundary.
No Ball! Tossed up, on leg stump. Root defends it out. A no ball is called for overstepping.
Very full, on leg stump. Root looks to defend but inside-edges it behind leg stump.
Floated it up, on leg. Root stays solid in defense.
Flighted up, on the rough outside leg and ends up around off stump. Root makes room to punch it off the back foot but can't find the gap on the off side.
Tossed up, outside leg and padded away by Root.
Flatter one, on the pads. Root tucks it off the back foot to square leg.
Length ball on off, Hameed blocks it right under his eyes.
On a length, outside off. Hameed dabs it towards backward point for a single.
Good-length ball outside off, Root leaves it alone.
Length ball on middle and leg, Root flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length around off, Hameed defends it down onto the deck.

TWO BYES! Good-length ball outside off, Haseeb Hameed looks to defend but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge. Rishabh Pant fails to collect the ball as it goes through his legs. The batters steal two byes.
Full and on leg, Joe Root reverse-sweeps it towards deep cover for a single.
Flatter ball on leg, Haseeb Hameed blocks it out.

OUT! TIMBER! Ravindra Jadeja provides India with a breakthrough after Lunch. Haseeb Hameed was batting so well but has to depart now. This is what Jadeja can do. He kept bowling on those rough patches and eventually finds success. This one was a tossed up ball on leg, it turned away sharply. Haseeb Hameed puts a big stride forward and looks to defend but misses. The ball goes past the tentative poke and disturbs the stumps behind him. England lose their third wicket now.
Howout: b Ravindra Jadeja

Commentary: Flatter one, on the pads. Pope taps it to short leg off the back foot.
Fuller one, aimed at the rough outside leg. Pope strides and gets his pad on it.
Quicker and flatter, on the stumps. Pope tries to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good-length ball on off, Root taps it past point for a single.
Good-length ball on off, Pope pushes it to cover.
Length ball outside off, Pope drives it but straight to the cover fielder.
On the pads, Pope flicks it to short mid-wicket.
On a length around off, Pope pushes it back to the bowler.
Off the mark! Touch fuller this time, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and creams it through covers for a couple of runs.
Flatter and full, on leg. Joe Root gets low and looks to sweep but misses. He gets hit on the pads. Pant appeals for an LBW but turned down by the umpire.
Flatter ball on leg, tucked on the leg side.
On leg, Root pads it away.
Quicker ball on the pads, Root blocks it out.
A low full toss on middle, Root sweeps it to deep square leg for a run.
Flatter ball on middle and leg, Pope watchfully blocks it out.
Good-length ball on middle, Root covers the stumps and plays it to mid on.
On a length around off, Root blocks it on the off side.
Length ball on off, Root taps it towards backward point for a quick single.
Good-length ball on off, Pope knocks it back to the bowler.

OUT! BOWLED! Inswing and pace and it proves to be too good for Ollie Pope. Good-length ball from Bumrah, on middle, angling in. Ollie Pope is beaten by the pace as he looks to play down the wrong line. The ball goes through the gate and shatters the stumps behind him. Pope could hear the death rattle behind him as well. Jasprit Bumrah gets his 100th Test wicket and what a better way than this to get it. India have done well to get two wickets in quick succession.
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Good-length ball on off, Jonny Bairstow defends it off the front foot.
Flatter one, outside leg stump. Root pads it away.
Jadeja comes around the wicket and tosses it up on off stump. Root pushes it to cover.
Flighted delivery, on middle. Root nudges it to mid-wicket.
A touch fuller and on middle. Root blocks it out.
Tossed up and again on middle stump. Root defends it off the front foot.

NOT OUT! Jadeja comes back over the wicket and floats one up around leg stump. Root goes down to sweep but misses the ball completely. He gets hit on the back leg and Ravindra Jadeja is confident that he has got his man. The review shows that the ball was pitching outside leg and hence the onfield decision stays.
Good-length ball, on off. Bairstow leaves it untouched.
Length again, on top of off. Bairstow stays solid in defense.

OUT! BOWLED! What a delivery from Jasprit Bumrah! The speedster bowls a perfect yorker, tailing in on middle stump. Jonny Bairstow is a good player but that one was too good, even for him. Bairstow tries to dig it out but before he can get his bat down, the ball goes through and shatters the middle stump. Bairstow has to depart without troubling the scorers. India are piling on the pressure now on the hosts.
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Good-length ball, angling into the body. Ali looks to block but gets hit in the abdominal region.
Length ball, around off. Ali defends it to cover-point.
Full and angling in at the toes. Ali looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up delivery, on middle. Root makes room and drives it towards cover for one.

OUT! CAUGHT! England are in all sorts of trouble now. Moeen Ali follows suit and joins Jonny Bairstow in the dressing room, as he too gets out on a duck. Jadeja gives this one more air and pulls back his length a bit. Jadeja bowls it on middle stump and the ball turns in a bit. Ali looks to defend but inside-edges it straight to short leg, where the substitute fielder, Suryakumar Yadav takes a sharp catch.
Howout: c sub Suryakumar Yadav b Ravindra Jadeja

Commentary: Quicker and faltter, on leg stump. Woakes keeps it out.
Floated it up, outside leg stump. Woakes pads it away.
Round-arm delivery, spilled down the leg side. Woakes leaves it alone.
Nicely tossed up, on middle and Woakes pushes it through covers for a couple.
Back of a length, around off. Root defends it to mid on.
Another length ball, angling in on middle stump. Root manages to keep it out.
Pitched up and pushed wider. Root shoulders arms.
On a length, outside off and shaping in. Joe Root with a tentative leave this time.
BEAUTY! Another inswinging yorker, on off stump. Joe Root somehow manages to get the toe end of his bat on it.
Length ball, on off. Root defends it out easily. A maiden over from Jasprit Bumrah.
Tossed up, on middle and kept out by Woakes.
Flatter one, on leg stump. Woakes inside edges it onto the pads.
Slower ball, full and on leg stump. Woakes defends it off the front foot.
Flatter ball on off, Woakes blocks it out on the off side.
On the pads, Woakes blocks it out.
Full and on leg, Woakes clips it to square leg.
Good-length ball on off, Root taps it to point.
Length ball on off, angling in. Root presses forward and defends it out.
Good-length ball outside off, Root lets it sail through.
Fuller in length, on off. Root pushes it to mid off.
Short ball on off, Root sways away from it.
A yorker, on middle. Joe Root does well to squeeze it out. Yet another maiden from Bumrah.
Flatter ball on leg, Woakes pads it away.
Full and on leg, Woakes blocks it out.
On the pads again, Woakes watchfully blocks it out.
Quicker one on leg, Woakes defends it off the front foot.
On middle, blocked out.
Loopy ball on middle, Woakes stays solid in defense.
On leg, Root clips it towards deep square leg for a single. 150 up for England.
Length ball on middle and leg, Woakes looks to work it on the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good-length ball on middle, angling in. Woakes pushes it back to the bowler.
Length ball on off, Woakes stays solid in defense.
On middle, blocked on the leg side.
Fuller in length, outside off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Good-length ball around off, Root plays it to cover.
On a length around off, Root blocks it out.
Outside off, Root dabs it down to third man for a single.
Length ball on leg, Woakes glances it to square leg for one.
Length ball, down the leg side. Root looks to flick but misses. Rishabh Pant does well to dive to his left to stop the ball.
On leg, Root looks to work it on the leg side but misses. He gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls on the leg side and the batters take a leg bye.
Short of a length, on off. Root dabs it past backward point for a couple of runs.
Full and outside off, left alone by Root.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fuller in length, on middle and leg. Joe Root pushes it towards long on for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Root presses forward and blocks it out.
Good-length ball on middle, blocked out.
On the pads, Root clips it to deep square leg. He retains the strike by picking up a single.
Fuller delivery, angling on the pads. Root flicks it to deep square leg for one.
Good-length ball, on off. Woakes taps it to short mid-wicket.
Pitched up, on middle and leg. Woakes pushes it to mid on.
Length again and right on the money. Chris Woakes defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller delivery, on middle and that one reversed a bit. Woakes looks to drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat and through mid-wicket. The batters get a couple.
Short ball, angling down leg stump. Woakes ducks under it.
Siraj drifts onto the pads again and Root flicks it fine. Umesh Yadav runs around from deep square leg and puts in the dive to keep it to a couple.
Back of a length, outside off. Root hops back and pats it to deep point for a single.
Shortish ball, swinging down the leg side. Woakes looks to pull but misses.

THREE LEG BYES! This one is angled in from outside off and comes back in a long way. Chris Woakes looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. Mohammed Siraj lets out a huge appeal but the umpire turns it down. The ball rolls on the off side and the batsmen sneak in the single. There is a shy at the bowler's end and there's no one backing up. The batters get two overthrows as well, resulting in a total of three leg byes.
Length ball, on the pads. Root flicks it to square leg.
Length again, on off. Root keeps it out.
FOUR! Nicely played! Fuller in length, on leg. Chris Woakes whips it off his pads through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Woakes looks to defend but miscues. The ball goes off the outer half towards backward point for a couple of runs.
Good-length ball on middle, Woakes pushes it back to the bowler.
SAFE! Another one on the pads and this one is bowled slower. Woakes looks to clip it on the leg side but top edges it behind square on the leg side. The ball lands safe and they cross for a single.
Length ball, on middle. Root defends it out.
Good-length ball, on off. Root opens the face of the bat and steers it past backward point for a run.
Length ball, angling on the pads. Root flicks it to short square leg.
Back of a length and on middle. Root nudges it to short mid-wicket.
On a good length, around off. Root stays solid in defense.
Pitched up, around off and angling into the right-hander. Root keeps it out to mid on.
Good-length ball and again on off. Root defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Classy from Joe Root. Pitched up, outside off and Root leans into the cover drive. Root gets it through cover-point and the ball races into the fence.
Fired in, full and around leg stump. Woakes pads it out.
Flatter one, on leg stump. Woakes defends it off the back foot. No ball signalled by the umpire as Jadeja has overstepped.
Flatter again and kept out again by Woakes.
Floated it up, outside leg. Woakes gets his pad on it.
Tossed up, outside leg again and once again Woakes pads it away.
Flatter delivery, around middle. Woakes taps it on the off side.
Jadeja tosses it up outside leg, looking for the rough patch. Woakes strides out and pads it away.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! India do not take the new ball, gives Shardul Thakur a go before taking it and he has delivered yet again. He bowls a good-length ball on the fifth stump channel, Joe Root stays deep in the crease and looks to cut it away. He is perhaps a bit too late into his shot. The ball goes off the inside half of the bat and shatters the stumps. England lose their best batsman and India into the ascendancy now.
Howout: b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: Good-length ball on middle, Overton blocks it out.
Length ball outside off, Overton taps it to cover.
Good-length ball on off, Overton blocks it off the front foot.
On a length outside off, Overton pushes it to the off side.
Outside off, Overton plays it towards point and keeps the strike.
Fuller in length, on off. Overton jams it out.
Good-length ball, outside off. Overton lets it sail through.
On a length outside off, Overton blocks it out from the crease.

DROPPED! Back of a length, around off. Craig Overton hops and looks to defend but miscues. The ball goes off the outside edge towards the third slip fielder. Ajinkya Rahane mistimes his dive to his right and spills it out. Two runs taken.
The skills that Bumrah possess! Follows a short ball with a yorker on middle, Overton flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short ball on leg, Overton ducks under it.
Good-length ball on middle, Woakes blocks it on the off side.
Length ball, outside off. Woakes taps it towards point.
On the pads, Woakes whips it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Outside off, Woakes plays it to the slip cordon.
Fuller in length, outside off. Woakes slices his drive past backward point for a couple of runs.
On leg, Woakes clips it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Good-length ball on off, Overton defends it towards mid on.
Short of a length, on off. Overton fends the ball on the leg side.

NOT OUT! The review turns out to be a fruitful one for Craig Overton. Fullish delivery, angling in on leg stump. Overton gets caught on the crease and the ball skids on to hit the pads. A huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger in a flash. The replay shows that the ball was doing too much and would have gone on to miss leg stump. Craig Overton survives, for now.
Full-length ball, on off. Overton pushes it towards covers.
Full again, on off. Overton pushes it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on middle. Overton tucks it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a change from Virat Kohli. Brings Umesh Yadav and he does not disappoint. He bowls a full-length ball on middle. Chris Woakes flicks it low in the air and towards short mid-wicket. KL Rahul takes a fine low catch to his left and that will be it for the second session. The umpires call for Tea.
Howout: c KL Rahul b Umesh Yadav

Commentary: Length ball down the leg side, Robinson leaves it alone.
Full and on middle, Robinson defends it out with a dead bat.
Good-length ball on off, Robinson knocks it to mid on.
FOUR! Nicely played! Length ball, outside off. Ollie Robinson cuts it late and past backward point for a boundary.
Short of a length on middle. Robinson takes his eyes off the ball and looks to sway away from it. But gets hit on the shoulder.
Good-length ball on middle, clipped through mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length, on middle, rising off the deck. Robinson dabs it to the man at third slip.
Short ball on middle and leg, Robinson sways away from it.
Short of a length, outside off. Ollie Robinson lets it be.
On a length on off, Robinson taps it to cover.
Bumrah goes full this time, on middle. Ollie Robinson negotiates with it comfortably.
Good-length ball on off, Overton blocks it out.
On middle, Overton flicks it to short mid-wicket.
On a length on leg, Overton looks to turn it on the leg side but gets hits on the thigh pad.
Short ball on off, Overton sits under it.
Slower ball from Umesh Yadav, on off. Craig Overton prods and looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge towards the slip cordon.

FOUR! Craig Overton has no idea what happened there. Short of a length on off, Overton pushes the ball away from the body and gets a big edge. The ball goes past the slip cordon and races away to the third man boundary.
Tossed up delivery, kept out by Robinson.
Full and straight. Robinson defends it out.
Floated it up, around leg. Robinson pads it away.
Flighted delivery, on leg. Robinson defends it off the front foot.
Slower and fuller, on off. Robinson blocks it out.
Flatter ball on off, Robinson blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Overton defends it solidly off the front foot.
Some movement straightaway! Good-length ball on off, nipping away. Craig Overton does well to block it out.
Beaten! Good-length ball outside off, nipping away. Overton looks to defend but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Good-length ball, on off. Overton covers the stumps and pushes it back to the bowler.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! The second new ball does the trick. Umesh Yadav serves a good-length ball on off, nipping away from the batter. Craig Overton gets squared up as he looks to defend. The ball hits his elbow and goes on to rattle the stumps behind him. India just a wicket away now from getting a victory. Overton is in deep pain on his way back to the pavilion.
Howout: b Umesh Yadav

Commentary: Well played by Jimmy! Fuller in length, on middle. James Anderson clips it towards fine leg for a single.
Short of a length, on off. Anderson hops and blocks it out.
An inswinging yorker from Bumrah, on middle. James Anderson clips it towards square leg for a single. Anderson will be a relieved man.
Length ball, on off. Robinson pushes it to extra cover.
Nasty bouncer! Short ball on middle, angling from off. Ollie Robinson does well to duck underneath.
Good-length ball on leg, Robinson looks to tuck it on the leg side but gets hit on the pads.
Length ball on leg, Robinson inside-edges it to fine leg. He denies the single at first but then takes it as Anderson calls for it.
Good-length ball on off. Robinson shuffles across and exposes the stumps. He blocks it out on the off side.
FOUR! Nice shot! Length ball on middle, Ollie Robinson pushes it past mid on for a boundary.
Short ball on middle, Robinson sits under it.
Short of a length on off. Robinson blocks it out.
Short of a length again, on off. Robinson looks to dab it down to third man but gets beaten.

Was there any glove on it? Yes, there was. Slower and shorter on middle and leg. Ollie Robinson looks to pull but miscues. The ball goes off the gloves towards the keeper. But the ball falls well short of Rishabh Pant. James Anderson sprints across to take the single.
Length ball, on off. Robinson pats it back to the bowler.
A quick bumper, on leg. Robinson ducks under it.
Very full, on off. Robinson manages to keep it out.
Back of a length, around off. Robinson defends it to point.
Full and wide. Robinson squeezes it uppishly to the right of gully. Ajinkya Rahane makes a good diving stop to his right.
Another short ball, on middle and leg. Robinson ducks under it well. Anderson tries to sneak a bye but there isn't one. Rishabh Pant fires a throw at the striker's end but misses.
Length ball, on the hips. Anderson keeps it out on the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! That is it! Back of a length, on off and angling away. James Anderson hops back and has a poke at it. Anderson gets the faint edge and Rishabh Pant makes no mistake behind the stumps. The umpire gives it out but Anderson reviews it. UltraEdge shows that indeed there was an edge. INDIA WIN BY 157 RUNS.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Umesh Yadav
